title: corn bread
directions: Stir first 6 ingredients until well blended.
In medium iron skillet, add 3/4 tablespoon oil; heat until hot.
Add bread batter and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Then broil until top is brown.

title: spritz cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add orange juice and egg yolk.

title: eskimo pie(a special dessert)
directions: In 1/4 cup water, soften gelatin; mix egg yolks with sugar, milk, salt and vanilla in top of a double boiler.
Cook slowly until thick and mixture coats a spoon.
Add softened gelatin and stir until well mixed.
Cool.
When partially thickened, fold in stiffly, beaten egg whites and then thick whipped cream.
Sprinkle 1/2 grated chocolate over bottom of 11 x 6-inch pan.
Cover with gelatin mixture.
Top with rest of grated chocolate.
Cover with waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in ovensafe dish.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: horseradish mold
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool until it starts to jell. Add horseradish, salt and whipped cream.
Pour into mold and let set.
Good accompaniment with beef.

title: wine coolers
directions: Mix one part wine with two parts seltzer and add a splash of fruit juice (such as orange or pineapple).
Has 8 calories per ounce.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix dry jello, Cool Whip and sour cream.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: beef stuffed bell peppers
directions: Combine salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, oats, egg, 1/3 cup catsup and onion.
Add to ground beef, mixing thoroughly.
Pack 1/2 cup meat mixture into each pepper half.
Place peppers in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top meat with 2 teaspoons catsup.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fried cabbage(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Over moderate heat, fry the onion in oil until lightly browned, stirring to prevent scorching.
Add tomatoes, salt and curry powder; continue stirring for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add cabbage, carrots and pepper; mix well.
Pour in about half a cup of water. Cover the pot, reduce heat and simmer until liquid is absorbed and cabbage is still slightly crunchy.

title: apple salad
directions: In heavy boiler, combine flour, sugar, pineapple, whipping cream and butter.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine, stirring until melted.
Refrigerate mixture to cool.
Place apples in serving bowl; fold in flour and pineapple mixture.
Garnish salad with nuts and cherries; chill.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mom's lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and garlic powder in oil; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, sauce and seasonings.
Simmer for 30 minutes uncovered. In bottom of greased pan, place 1/2 meat sauce and arrange 1/2 lasagna over top.
Spoon 1/2 of Parmesan cheese, Cheddar and cottage cheese over top, then layer lasagna, cheeses and meat sauce.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy apples
directions: Let cheese and oleo come to room temperature.
Add sugar and flour.
Spread pie filling in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cheese mixture over top and spread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: On a serving plate, layer, in order:

Bean Dip; avocado - mashed with lemon juice, added; sour cream; sprinkle with taco seasoning; sprinkle with grated cheddar and monterey jack cheeses; chopped bunch of green onions; add chopped (finely) tomatoes; top with chopped black olives.
Serve with chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Beat eggs and add mayonnaise, cheese, soup and onion together.
Add broccoli; mix together. Melt margarine and add crackers.
Put broccoli mixture in casserole bowl.
Add cracker mixture on
top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: big mac sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given, dough will be soft.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Dice zucchini; blend oil and zucchini in blender.
In bowl, cream oleo and sugar.
Add zucchini and oil, eggs and vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients and sour milk alternately.
Pour into greased, floured pan, 9 x 13-inch or 2 loaf pans.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Frost or use powdered sugar or serve plain.
Freezes well.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325° until top is evenly brown.

title: homemade peach ice cream
directions: Combine 1/2 cup of sugar, gelatin and half of the cream.
Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into egg; mix well.
Return to remaining mixture.
Cook and stir until thick, about 1 minute.
Chill.
Add remaining cream, vanilla, almond extract and salt.
Combine peaches and 3/4 cup of sugar.
Add to chilled mixture.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add salt and sprinkle of pepper.
Put beans in glass casserole dish and microwave for 5 minutes.
When onion and garlic are soft, combine with beans and mix.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Chop cauliflower, broccoli and onions up together.
Mix mayonnaise sugar, oil, vinegar and dressing.
Pour dressing mixture over chopped up vegetables.
Stir well.
Refrigerate until ready to be served.

title: chyrl's broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine corn, broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup crackers, 2 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole dish. Combine 1/4 cup of crackers and remaining butter.
Sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake uncovered in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: kahlua cheesecake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; refrigerate until partially set.
Cream cream cheese and sugar together.
Add Jell-O to cheese mixture.
Whip the cream; add the Kahlua and whipped cream, folding into the cheese-Jell-O mixture.
Spoon carefully into a chocolate crumb crust.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain and mash and put in casserole dish.
Add cooked rice, soup and Velveeta.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
The last 10 minutes of baking take out and add cracker crumbs to top, return to oven and finish cooking.

title: do ahead chicken divan
directions: Combine chicken and salt in a Dutch oven; add enough water to cover chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Remove chicken and cool slightly.
(Reserve broth for other uses.)
Bone chicken and chop.
Cook broccoli according to package; drain well.
Arrange broccoli in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine soup with next 5 ingredients.
Spoon 1/2 sauce over broccoli.
Place chicken over this and pour remaining sauce over.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake 5 more minutes. Serves 8.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: smoked salmon ball
directions: Drain, flake, and remove skin and bone from salmon.
Mix well: salmon, cheese, juice, onion, horseradish, salt and liquid smoke. Roll in pecans and parsley.
Wrap and refrigerate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and onion; mix together.
Crisp bacon
and crumble into broccoli/onion mixture.
Mix sugar and mayonnaise; mix into salad mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: In mixing bowl beat together sugar, pumpkin, oil and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add and stir until smooth.
Do not mix any more than necessary.
Blend in nuts and drop onto lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: swedish meat cakes
directions: Mix lightly; make into cakes.
Roll in flour and brown in fat in skillet.
Add 1 1/2 cups of tomato sauce or stock.
Put in covered casserole and bake 45 minutes.
Serve with border of rice.

title: corned beef supper
directions: Layer potatoes and carrots in casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Layer minced corned beef over potatoes and carrots, then add layer of onion.
Next add layer of cabbage and dot with butter.
Mix soup and sauce and pour over vegetables.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients and put in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and put on top.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: easy rolls
directions: Place water in bowl. Add salt and set aside. Mix yeast into dry cake mix. Add water. Add flour gradually. Mix and knead until smooth (can use a mixer). Knead and cover for 1 hour. Let mix rise in a warm place. Shape into rolls. Let stand until double in size. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add nuts and fruit; toss.
Mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, then pumpkin.
Add water and flour, alternating to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Add water and cook approximately 1 hour.
Add other ingredients and cook until done.
(Remove ham hock from soup when half done and tear ham from bone; put back into soup.)

title: frost on the pumpkin pie
directions: In a small bowl, combine all crust ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Reserve 2 tablespoons of crumbs for topping.
Press remaining in pie pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil this together
until
it
forms
a soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add
1 tablespoon vanilla and 1/2 cup peanut butter. Beat with spoon until creamy.
Pour in buttered pan and cut when cool.

title: church window cookies
directions: In heavy saucepan (or top of double boiler), melt together chocolate chips and butter.
Cool.
Stir in nuts and marshmallows. Mix well.
Sprinkle coconut on waxed paper.
Turn out chocolate mix onto waxed paper; shape into log and sprinkle with coconut remaining on waxed paper.
Roll in waxed paper and refrigerate 24 hours.
Slice into desired thickness.
Makes 3 logs.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add lemon extract.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Fold in 7-Up.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts on wax paper.
Wrap and store in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin-mincemeat bread(recipe created by doris.)
directions: Mix the sugar, eggs, oil and pumpkin first in a large bowl. Mix in another bowl the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and salt.
In a pan, mix the water and mincemeat.
Bring to a boil. Add the raisins.
Combine the first two mixtures and add mincemeat.
Grease and flour five 1 pound coffee cans. Fill half full.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool completely and shake just enough to slice each piece. Cover can with the plastic lid to ensure freshness.
Freeze in cans, if needed.
Makes nice gifts. Just wrap can in foil and add bow!

title: bran muffins
directions: Dissolve the baking soda in 2 cups boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
With electric mixer, cream butter and sugar and beat in eggs.
Stir in by hand the remaining ingredients.
Finally, stir in soda water.
Keep batter in refrigerator.
Bake in muffin pan for 30 minutes at 375°.
Batter will keep for about 1 month.
This is also good with pecans or raisins added as you start to bake.

title: walnut chews
directions: Crush Special K into 1 1/2 cups and set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, and salt.
Set aside.
Place margarine or butter and sugar in large mixer bowl; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add sifted ingredients.
Mix until thoroughly combined.
Stir in Special K and nuts.
Drop by level tablespoons onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately from baking sheets onto a wire rack.

title: blue cheese puffs
directions: Over a low heat, melt cheese and butter; set aside.
Open tube of biscuits and cut each into 4 pieces.
Dip each piece into the cheese mixture.
Place in a pie plate and bake per directions on biscuit package.
Serve with a glass of wine.

title: garlic sauce for roast
directions: Heat oil.
Chop up garlic.
Brown garlic
in oil for 2 minutes.
Add some sauce from roast; season with black pepper. Simmer for 1 minute.
Mix flour with water and add to sauce to thicken.

title: candy yams
directions: Boil potatoes and let cool, then peel them.
Slice in a pan. In a pot, bring margarine, brown sugar and syrup to a boil. Sprinkle cinnamon over potatoes and then pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brown sugar crispies
directions: In large bowl, beat together butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Shape dough to form two 12-inch long rolls; wrap in wax paper.
Freeze several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°. Cut each roll into 1/4-inch thick slices; bake on ungreased cookie sheets 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet, then remove to wire cooling rack.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: something, nothing, everything cookies
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Mix the next 4 ingredients thoroughly and gradually add to first part.
Add the last 3 ingredients.
Stir with fork.
Shape into walnut size balls.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: breakfast egg and ham casserole
directions: Spread margarine on one side of bread; remove crusts and cut into small cubes.
Combine cubes, ham, cheese, salt and pepper; stir well.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir in milk.
Add egg mixture to ham mixture; stir well.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil noodles until tender, then drain and put into a casserole dish.
Cut blocks of cheese into small chunks and mix the cheese and soup in the dish of noodles; stir.
Mix in the butter, milk and salt.
Place in oven at 300° until cheese is fully melted. Take out of oven and stir.
Slice a few pieces of sharp Cheddar cheese and place on top of macaroni.
Place into oven until cheese on top melts.
Take out of oven and allow time to cool.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 1/3 cup juice.
Cut chicken into chunks.
Cook spaghetti, drain and set aside.
In a large skillet or wok, stir for 2 minutes oil, ginger, chicken and garlic.
Add pineapple chunks, carrots and pepper.
Cover and steam 2 to 3 minutes until tender-crisp.
Stir in spaghetti.

title: cool and creamy coconut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: cheesy corn jalapeno muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Butter a 12 - cup muffin tin with the softened butter and set aside.

title: rocky road peanut butter squares
directions: Heat syrup and sugar to boiling in heavy 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Immediately remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until melted.
Place cereal in a large bowl. Pour peanut butter mixture over cereal, stirring until well coated.
Cool 2 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows.
Press mixture in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle with peanuts.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Boil strawberries and vinegar hard for 1 minute.
Add sugar and boil 20 minutes.
Let set until cold.
Put in jars.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Saute spinach in butter until limp.
Stir in flour and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Combine eggs, cream, salt and pepper and mix well.
Stir in cheese and spinach.
Pour into pastry shells and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in oil in skillet.
Reduce heat.
Add water; simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Combine cornstarch, salt, brown sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce in bowl; mix well. Pour over pork.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Add green pepper, onions and pineapple chunks.
Simmer for 4 to 5 minutes longer. Stir in Kitchen Bouquet.
Serve over rice or Chinese noodles. Serves 4.

title: wild vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Cook meat in oil 5 minutes.
Mix flour with tomato juice and stir into meat.
Add tomatoes, onions and spices.
Cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Grease 2 medium casseroles. Layer noodles, meat mixture, then cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut tops from green peppers; discard seeds and membranes. Chop enough of the tops to make 1/4 cup; set aside. Cook the whole peppers, uncovered, in boiling water for 5 minutes; invert to drain well. Sprinkle insides of peppers lightly with salt.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta just until done; rinse and drain.
Slice black olives and mix with pasta.
Mix dressing and pour over pasta. Chill and serve.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Stew chicken; reserve broth.
Cook broccoli in chicken broth. Remove chicken from bones. Layer chicken and broccoli in glass casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over layered chicken and broccoli.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mocha almond roll
directions: In a small bowl combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in water, 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla and almond.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Grease a 15 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with waxed paper.
Grease again.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: molassas oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening. Add eggs, mix well.
Add molassas and beat. Combine flour, spices, and soda. Add to cream mixture, alternate adding with oatmeal. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 min.

title: butter and cheese pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Toss hot pasta with several tablespoons real butter.
When melted, grate fresh Romano or Parmesan cheese.
Toss.

title: creamed corn
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Butter to taste over the top.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown.

title: banana split crumb cake
directions: Mix together margarine and 1/2 cup sugar with graham cracker crumbs.
Reserve 1/4 cup of this mixture.
Press remaining mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Slice round steak into 1-inch strips; brown in oil.
Slice onion into strips.
Slice pepper into 1-inch strips.
Add onion and pepper to meat; brown, then drain oil.
Add Lipton onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Put lid on; cook on medium-low for 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: ham ball(servings:  8)
directions: Using food processor, coarsely chop ham.
Then finely chop onion and raisins.
Combine ham, onion and raisins using just enough mayonnaise for all ingredients to be consistent.
Form into a ball.
Mix cream cheese with small amount of milk (to make spreadable); add a dash of Tabasco sauce.
Spread over ham ball. Dash of cayenne pepper on top.
Garnish with parsley.
Lightly chill and serve with a crisp cracker.
Suggested wine:
Chablis or Chardonnay.
Serving Ideas:
Colors of red, green and white.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Make pudding according to directions on box.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes(crock-pot cooking)
directions: Put half of ham, potatoes and onions in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining half.

title: turkey and dressing
directions: Cook turkey in water with bouillon cubes for 5 to 6 hours (or until done) at 350°.
Remove turkey.
Set broth aside to cool. Carve turkey and arrange on platter.
Cover.
In large bowl, combine cornbread crumbs, light bread, onions, eggs and seasonings.
Add broth and mix well.
Work well with your hands, blending out bread lumps.
Mixture should be very "soupy".
Pour into turkey roaster and cook for approximately 1 hour.
Stir once or twice during this time.
Cook until lightly browned.
Serve with turkey.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all but butter.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Stir in butter; pour into 9-inch baked shell or graham cracker pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Spread over pie.
Sprinkle with coconut and brown.

title: nacho cheese
directions: Cube cheese.
Place in microwavable dish for 3 minutes. Remove from oven and stir.
Place back in microwave for 2 more minutes.
While cheese is melting, brown the ground beef and smoked sausage.
Remove cheese from oven and add salsa, beef and sausage.
Place back in microwave 2 minutes or until hot as desired.

title: mushroom rounds
directions: Toast bread rounds.
Cook scallions in butter until soft.
Add chopped or ground mushrooms and cook over low heat until water is evaporated.
Sprinkle with flour, stirring to blend.
Continue cooking.
Add cream and cook until very thick.
Stir as necessary. Remove from heat when thick; add all remaining ingredients.
Cool. Spread over rounds.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400°. Freezes well.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add beaten eggs, milk and drained corn.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot grease and cook until done.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Pull out stems and chop.
Saute onion, celery and stems until tender.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Fill caps with mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Heat in oven on cookie sheet.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick of the butter with the graham cracker crumbs. Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: wedding rings
directions: Cut sandwich bread into rounds with 6-ounce frozen juice can or small cookie cutter.
Remove center with thimble.
Spread each with whipped cream cheese and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese. Make 3 rounds per slice.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans and soup in a casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven until it bubbles.
Add French fried onion rings on top.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese in bowl with mixer until light and fluffy. Add peanut butter and milk; beat until smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into pie shell. Sprinkle with peanuts. Freeze until firm. Serve frozen. Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in a thick bottom 4-quart pan.
Cook on high heat, adding peanuts when temperature reaches 240°.
When temperature reaches 300°, remove from fire.
Stir in baking soda and pour immediately on greased aluminum foil.
Smooth over and rake down only once.
Break into pieces when hard.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook all ingredients until it thickens good.
Let cool thoroughly.
Pour mixture into 2 baked pie shells or 1 big pie shell.
Add strawberries.
Top with Dream Whip.

title: skor truffle
directions: Bake cake.
Make puddings.
Freeze Skor bars.
Crumble with food processor or in a plastic bag and hammer.
Begin layering Skor bars, 1/2 crumbled cake, 1 pudding and 1 Cool Whip.
Repeat and top with Skor bars.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add soups and milk.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Grease casserole.
Put in uncooked noodles.
Pour ground beef mixture over noodles.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add flour, coconut and vanilla.
Bake in stem pan at 325° or in 2 oblong loaf pans for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pink popcorn surprise
directions: Measure popped corn into large buttered bowl.
In top of double boiler over hot water, heat marshmallows, butter and salt, stirring frequently until marshmallows melt and mixture is smooth. Stir in food color.
Pour mixture over corn in bowl.
Toss gently to coat.
With buttered hands, quickly shape mixture around lollipops into 3-inch balls.
Put into small bags with ties on top.

title: poppy seed cheese bread
directions: Slice bread lengthwise and butter.
Combine all ingredients, except poppy seed.
Spread on bread and then sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until toasty brown.

title: chicken bites
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in chicken, celery, pimento and set aside.
Separate dough into rectangles.
Spread about 1/4 cup cream cheese mixture over each rectangle, leaving 1/2-inch margin on either side.
Roll dough, starting at side with filling to edge.
Pinch seams to seal. Brush with egg and sprinkle with seed.
Cut each roll into 5 pieces.
Place seam side down on lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: molasses glazed hens(makes 4 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle the hens with salt and pepper and put in a shallow roasting pan.
Roast 20 minutes.
Combine the ginger and the molasses.
Brush some of the molasses mixture over the hens.
Continue roasting until done, about 25 minutes more.
Baste occasionally with the molasses glaze and the pan juices.

title: pasta and sausage soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven or saucepan over medium heat, heat sausages and 1/4 cup water to boiling.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes. Remove cover and continue cooking, turning sausages frequently until water evaporates and sausages are well browned, about 20 minutes.
Remove sausages to paper towels to drain.
Cut sausages into 1/4-inch thick slices.
In drippings remaining in Dutch oven over medium heat, cook green peppers, onions and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Return sausages to Dutch oven; add tomatoes with their liquid, macaroni, sugar, Worcestershire, bouillon and 6 cups water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 25 minutes until macaroni is very tender, stirring occasionally.
Skim off fat from soup. Makes about 12 cups or 8 main dish servings.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip pieces of chicken in melted margarine. Roll in bread crumbs. Place in baking dish (I use a cookie sheet). Sprinkle with remaining seasonings. Pour remaining margarine over chicken. Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Enjoy!

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Cover bottom of 14-inch round pizza pan, overlapping slightly.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt the butter.
Add molasses and sugar.
Cook until brittle when tested in cold water.
Pour gradually, while stirring, over popcorn in large kettle.
Salt should be sprinkled over corn just before pouring the molasses.
Shape into balls as gently as possible.

title: chicken croissants
directions: Bake chicken breasts until done.
Remove from oven.
In casserole dish, place crescent rolls out flat.
Place 1 breast in the middle of each roll.
Place cheese on top of chicken breast. Sprinkle diced onions on top of cheese.
Wrap entire breast with roll.
Continue the same process with the remaining chicken and rolls.
Spoon cream of mushroom soup over each croissant (chicken and all) repeat process.
Then place in oven at 350° and bake until rolls are golden.
Remove and serve.
It's great!!!

title: carrot casserole
directions: Boil carrots until tender.
Drain liquid and save.
Mash carrots and season with butter, salt and pepper.
Add crackers and cheese and mix well.
Add liquid to moisten.
Put in baking dish, sprinkle with little more cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel apple and orange and cut into small pieces.
Drain pineapple and cherries.
Combine all ingredients.
May serve now, or later.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer soup in the chicken broth for 5 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Let set for 1 hour in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs and 1 cup melted margarine.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Put yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in refrigerator and let stand overnight.
Roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Let rise.
Bake at 400°.

title: lemon marsala chicken
directions: Thinly slice chicken, then flour chicken.
Saute in olive oil until golden.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper.
Remove from pan and put into baking dish.
In pan over low heat, melt margarine.
Stir in flour and brown.
Stir in wines, parsley, garlic and lemon juice.
Stir into gravy consistency.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: corn relish
directions: Put 2 tablespoons pickling spice in a tied cheesecloth.
Boil corn for 5 minutes.
Cut from cob.
Measure and mix all ingredients with 1 cup of water. Simmer 20 minutes.
Bring to boiling.
Pour into hot jars and seal at once.

title: favorite meat loaf(microwave cooking directions)
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard in a small bowl; set aside.
Combine egg, onion, oatmeal, ground beef, salt and pepper in a mixing bowl.
Add half of the tomato mixture and blend thoroughly.
Shape into an oval loaf and place in an oblong microproof baking dish.
Make a depression in top of loaf. Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat.
Cook, uncovered, on Medium for 25 to 30 minutes, until center is cooked.
Cover meat; let stand for about 10 minutes before serving.

title: jessica's sugar cookies
directions: Mix softened butter and eggs.
Add to the mixture the sugar, vanilla, cream of tartar and baking soda.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled potatoes in boiling water until tender; drain. Add cream cheese, sour cream, onion salt, salt and pepper.
Beat until light and fluffy; cool.
Cover; place in refrigerator (will keep several days).

title: wine scampi(microwave)
directions: To defrost scampi, place in a single layer on layer of paper towels; cook 1 minute and 30 seconds or until almost thawed.
Set aside.
In a 1 1/2-quart (8 or 9-inch round) baking dish, combine butter, garlic, wine and parsley.
Cook, uncovered, 2 minutes. Add scampi and cook, uncovered, 2 minutes or until hot, stirring once.

title: marlo minted walnuts
directions: Combine sugar, salt, water and syrup in saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat until syrup forms a small ball when dipped in cool water.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows and extract.
Stir until all marshmallows are melted, then add nuts and stir gently until nuts are evenly coated.
Pour out on cookie sheet and separate with fork.
Cool and store in tightly covered container. Refrigerate.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into individual dishes or a large serving bowl.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: scramble egg muffins
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage:
drain.
In a bowl, beat the eggs. Add onion, green pepper, salt pepper and garlic powder.
Stir in sausage and cheese.
Spoon by 1/3 cupfuls into greased muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 20 - 30 minutes or until a knife is inserted near the center comes out clean.
Yield:

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Mix all of the ingredients except tortillas with salt and pepper to taste (no cheese yet).
Dip tortillas in warm chicken broth and line bottom of a baking dish (large).
Use 6 tortillas per layer.
Then add chicken mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers again, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: In saucepan combine chocolate and condensed milk and butter. Heat over low fire until chocolate is melted. Put marshmallows and nuts in a large bowl.
Spread mixture on wax paper in pan.
Chill.

title: plate peach pie
directions: Put sliced peaches in uncooked pie crust.
Mix egg yolks, sugar, margarine and flour.
Pour over peaches and bake at 325° until golden brown.
Top with beaten egg whites, put back in oven and brown egg whites.

title: party reubens(appetizer)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Spread 1/4 teaspoon butter on top of each bread slice.
Place a half slice of corned beef on each slice, folding beef to fit.
Top each with 1/2 teaspoon sauce mixture, 1 teaspoon sauerkraut and a piece of cheese.
Place bread slices on baking sheet; broil 8 inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: opera nut creams
directions: Combine sugar, cream, milk, corn syrup and salt in a 4-quart saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil on medium heat.
Place thermometer in mixture and cook to 236° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat; cool to 110° (lukewarm), without stirring.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture loses its gloss.
Add nuts.

title: peanut butter play clay
directions: In medium bowl stir together all ingredients until blended. Knead about 30 seconds until smooth and plastic.
Use immediately or store in refrigerator in airtight container until ready to use. Makes about 1 and 3/4 cups.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Spread evenly in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Blend together thoroughly the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix in eggs, coffee and butter.

title: low-fat quick meal
directions: Boil chicken broth.
Add frozen vegetables.
Keep at a slow boil until vegetables are soft.
In a separate pot, make your spaghetti.
When all is done, strain spaghetti.
Pour the vegetables and broth over spaghetti and enjoy an almost zero fat meal.

title: chocolate chip dessert pizza
directions: In medium size bowl, combine flour, salt, baking soda and oatmeal.
Set aside.
In separate mixing bowl combine sugars, eggs, vanilla and butter flavored Crisco.
Beat until creamed.
Gradually add combined dry ingredients to creamed mixture until well blended. Stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon mixture onto foil lined 14 inch pizza pan.
Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from the oven and cool.
Invert cooled cookie onto back side of another pizza pan, then flip over onto serving tray.
Decorate with frosting if desired.

title: sunday morning brunch
directions: Mix eggs, salt, milk, mustard, and diluted soup. Layer bread, sausage, cheese, and egg mixture in a 9x13 pan.
Refrigerate over night. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8-12.

title: wheaties cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Add coconut and Wheaties last.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: nuts 'n bolts
directions: Mix margarine, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, savor salt and onion salt.
Then mix dry ingredients.
Toast at 250° for 1 to 2 hours.
Stir often.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Beat milk, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Pour into pre-cooked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add sugar until stiff.
Spread on pie.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until meringue is browned slightly.

title: elizabeth bale's corn pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add to corn.
Add beaten eggs and milk; mix well.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix, chill and eat.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown the pork chops.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together. Top this with the chops.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into deep, hot grease.
Fry until golden brown.
Serve hot with maple syrup.

title: christmas fruitcake
directions: Rinse raisins and drain on towel.
Pour boiling water over prunes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
DRAIN DRY, use scissors and cut up.
Combine nuts, rind, all fruits.
Pour juice over and let stand.

title: mexican chicken bake
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Mix soup, onion and chiles.
Place 1/2 Doritos in dish.
Next place 1/2 chicken.
Cover with soup mixture.
Repeat for 3 layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle red pepper, if you would like, over top.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Addition of a ham bone is the most important donation to the pot, for it adds real color and flavor not possible to achieve otherwise.
The next most important thing is to buy small, dark red beans, not kidney beans.
Most Acadian cooks like to bring theirs to a rolling boil for a couple of minutes, then let them soak in that same water overnight.
In the morning, bring to boil again and add all other ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer for at least 3 hours.
Beans should become very creamy, but most will remain whole.
Serve in profuse quantities ladled over fluffy rice.
Don't forget sliced raw onion rings and butter on top of each plate. Beans may be cooked with other pork meat or sausages.

title: raspberry syrup
directions: Combine 1 cup fresh or frozen raspberries or strawberries, powdered sugar and butter in a small nonstick skillet.
Gently heat through, stirring, and drizzle over pancakes.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Boil all ingredients except macaroni for 1/2 hour or until vegetables are done.
Add macaroni and cook 15 minutes, until done.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: In a large heavy pot, cook bacon until crisp and remove.
In bacon drippings, brown beef cubes.
Add soup, wine, garlic, bay leaf, parsley and bacon. Season to taste.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour. Stir occasionally.
Add onions and cook 1 hour longer or until tender. Remove bay leaf.
Serves 4 to 6.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: quick cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cooks fast.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend Bisquick, sausage and cheese by hand until sausage feels warm and all ingredients are blended.
Make small balls and bake in ungreased pan for 12 minutes at 450°.
Cut oven off and leave sausage balls in oven for another 5 minutes.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Trim crust from bread slices, spread margarine over one side of bread. Place bread slices, buttered side up in bottom of a lightly greased 13 x 9 pan. Set aside. Brown sausage in large skillet, stirring until it crumbles. Drain. Spoon sausage over bread. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine eggs, half and half, and salt. Pour over cheese. Cover and chill 8 hours or overnight. Remove from refrigerator, let stand covered for 15 minutes. Uncover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 8 servings.

title: rosy raspberry fizz
directions: Mash raspberries with a fork in a large bowl until raspberries are blended with their juice. Add pineapple juice, ice cream and sherbet. Stir well. Slowly pour in cream soda.

title: 5-layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs.
Mix together and press evenly in bottom of pan. Layer with butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and coconut flakes. Pour the Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Let cool and then cut.

title: fried dill pickles
directions: Dip pickles in batter and roll in flour; deep fry.
For sauce, use French horseradish, mustard, mayonnaise and garlic salt to taste.

title: chicken fried steak with creamed pan gravy
directions: Place steaks on a wax paper lined surface and cover with a second sheet of wax paper.
Pound steaks into 1/4 inch thick pieces and set to the side.
Line your work area with clean wax paper and make 1/2 cup pile of flour, then pile of corn meal, and then another 1/2 cup pile of flour.
To the last pile of flour, mix in the paprika, pepper, and salt.
In a shallow dish, beat together the water and eggs.
Cut steaks into 4 pieces.
Coat first in plain flour, then egg, then seasoned flour, and finally the cornmeal.
In a heavy skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the oil. When hot, brown up 2 pieces of steak at a time and more oil as needed.
Then all are browned, place all of the steak back into the skillet, cover, and cook for 15 minutes.
Remove steaks to a serving platter and pour off all but 3 tablespoons of the drippings.
Add 2 tablespoons of flour to the drippings and cook about 2 minutes.
Whisk in the broth, season with salt and pepper. Then add in the cream with a whisk.
When gravy bubbles, remove from heat.
Prepare the biscuits while the steak cooks according to the directions. Serve steaks and warm biscuits with gravy on top.

title: angel salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into dish.
Chill.

title: stromboli wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly spread one side of each Wrap with softened butter; sprinkle with 1 Tbsp. parmesan.
Arrange one fourth each of provolone, salami, capicolla (or ham) and roasted peppers over center of wraps, leaving border around edges. Sprinkle each wrap with one fourth of the mozzarella.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (190°C).
Place shelf on center level of oven.
Grease 12 medium muffin cups.
Cream together butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Peel ripe bananas and, using a fork, mash until no lumps remain.
Blend egg into creamed sugar-butter mixture, then mix into it the mashed bananas.
In hot water, dissolve baking soda.
Add it to sugar-bananas.
Combine sugar-banana mixture with flour and salt; stir.
Keep stirring only until blended, about 15 to 20 times maximum.
Mixture should be lumpy.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pan and bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: grandma gray's buttermilk candy
directions: Dissolve baking soda in butter.
In large saucepan, combine oleo, sugar, syrup and buttermilk, mixing well.
Cook over medium-low heat until mixture reaches firm ball stage when tested in cool water.
Use candy thermometer; cook at 242°.
Mixture will turn brown.
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat, cool slightly and beat until begins to thicken.
Add pecans and beat.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and chill.

title: mary ann's party potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and drain.
Add cream cheese and sour cream. Whip it all together until smooth and put into baking dish.
Just before baking, melt butter over top and add dash of paprika for looks.

title: beer cheese soup(serves 4)
directions: Melt the butter in a heavy soup pot. Add the onion and celery. Cook until just soft. Sprinkle on the flour and cook for 3 minutes, stirring frequently. Slowly whisk in first the broth, then the beer. Bring to a boil. Reduce the heat. Slowly whisk in the cheese. Add the mustard. Remove from the heat and serve immediately.

title: hungry horde pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta al dente in boiling water.
Drain.
Mix with half of the mayonnaise.
Add tuna, onion, olives and tomatoes.
Fold in remaining mayonnaise and season to taste with pepper and Season-All. Refrigerate, covered, at least 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix well; shape into balls and cook until done.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Stir until mixture holds together.
Knead briefly and roll out on floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° on ungreased pan.

title: spinach cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in oven at 350°.
Keep checking until done.

title: diet chili
directions: Combine meat, garlic, chili powder, onion, bell pepper, Sweet 'N Low, salt and Accent in skillet.
Brown well.
Add water and juice.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Freezes extra well.

title: cathedral lights marshmallow cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat.
Remove from heat. Add egg; mix well.
Cool slightly.
Mix marshmallows and nuts in large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over them; mix well.
Divide mixture in half.
On waxed paper sprinkled with confectioners sugar, shape each half into a roll approximately 8-inches long. Chill several hours.
Slice to serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Use 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine in pan. Cut fruit and place over margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over top of peaches.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Serve plain or with vanilla ice cream.

title: collins baked beans
directions: Fry bacon half done; remove from pan.
Saute onion and pepper in bacon fat.
Mix all ingredients except pineapple.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with pineapple and bake for 30 minutes or more.

title: black bean soup
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Pour into medium pan and bring to low boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30-40 minutes.
Serve topped with dollop of sour cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and milk, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter chips until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cool.

title: spinach corn bread
directions: Mix all and pour in greased iron skillet.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven for 3 to 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mike newman's mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, soup and chili.
Heat.
In a large casserole (9 x 13-inch), alternate broken tortilla chips, meat mixture and cheese; repeat.
Heat in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly, 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips and picante sauce.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, mix meat, eggs, green onions, onion, bread crumbs, milk, horseradish, salt, mustard and 1/4 cup catsup.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, shape meat mixture into 10 x 5-inch loaf, pressing firmly.
Spread remaining 1/2 cup catsup over loaf.
Bake 1 hour.
Garnish with green onion.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Mix hot water and milk.
When it is lukewarm, add shortening, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups flour and the other half cup, if needed.
Dough should not be too stiff.
When mixed, cover bowl firmly and place in refrigerator for several hours or 2 or 3 days.
Form into rolls; let rise and bake at 375°.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Grease 9 x 13 inch pan. Beat eggs, add white sugar, brown sugar, milk, salt and pumpkin spice. Pour into pan. Sprinkle 2 c. cake mix over pumpkin mixture. Melt oleo and drizzle over cake mix. Sprinkle nuts over all. Bake 1 hour and 35 minutes, test when knife inserted comes out clean.

title: aloha banana bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Mix oleo, eggs, milk and flavorings along with orange rind.
Combine with 1 cup mashed bananas and dry mixture.
Add coconut and nuts.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Slice Vienna bread in half long ways and take out middle. Shred or cut up middle of bread which you took out and mix with all ingredients.
Put back in bread.
Bake for approximately 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese - new jersey style
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender; drain.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk. Cook and stir until thick.
Add salt, pepper and cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Mix sauce with macaroni and egg.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until bubbly and browned.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: turkey and brown rice casserole
directions: Saute the onion, celery and green pepper in 3 tablespoons butter or margarine. Add soup and rest of the ingredients in a 2 1/2-quart casserole (or use 2 smaller ones to bake and 1 to freeze for later).

title: frozen strawberry refresher
directions: Combine daiquiri mix and orange juice in container of an electric blender; add enough ice to bring mixture to 5-cup level. Process until mixture is slushy.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 5 cups.

title: lumpia(egg roll)
directions: Brown ground beef or pork; drain fat.
In a large bowl, combine and mix all the ingredients, except lumpia wrappers.
Mix well.

title: shrimpie spread
directions: Spread cream cheese on luncheon plate.
Cover with shrimp. Cover with seafood sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: mystery crackers
directions: Pour the crackers into an airtight plastic container.
Pour oil over crackers.
Stir gently with a wooden spoon.
Sprinkle one packet of cream of chicken and one packet cream of mushroom soup over the crackers and stir gently every few hours with a wooden spoon.
Do not refrigerate.

title: supreme pizza
directions: Prepare pizza according to directions except do not cook yet. Cook sausage and drain.
Layer all ingredients, putting cheese last.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Oven temperatures will vary.

title: grammy labar's macaronis
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients; add hamburger.
Cook.
Add sugar, enough until it tastes sweet.
Cook noodles and cut sharp cheese into cubes.
Place noodles in roaster pan.
Pour sauce in and place cheese on top.
Bake at 375° to 400° until cheese is melted.

title: easy limon salad
directions: Mix lime jello according to directions on package.
Mix and cook lemon pudding according to package.
Soft set jello and cool pudding.
Use a wire whip and combine both mixtures.
Let set, preferably overnight.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pickled carrots
directions: Cook carrots, not too soft.
Cool.
Combine all ingredients. Marinate at least 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: strawberry roll
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Gradually add sugar, then water and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold into egg mixture.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Line with waxed paper, greased on both sides and extended over ends.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 13 minutes at 375°.
Turn out onto towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll up in towel.
Let cool.
Unroll; remove towel and roll up again.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Pour remaining ingredients into pan. Stir with spoon until blended.
Spread evenly in pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: elk roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast and put in ungreased roast pan with lid. Mix mushroom soup with 1 can condensed milk.
Add dry soup mix. Stir to mix well.
Pour over roast in 300° oven for 2 hours or until done.

title: apricot and currant chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in baking pan and sprinkle generously with salt, pepper and other desired seasoning. Add ginger and spread marmalade over chicken and pour apple and orange juices into pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add apricots and currants to chicken.
Sprinkle brown sugar and return to oven.
Baste often until chicken is brown and shiny, approximately 45 minutes.

title: best ever pancakes
directions: Put flours, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, and salt into a large bowl, stir to mix well and set aside. Whisk together the buttermilk, egg and oil, stir into the flour mixture to form a smooth batter. Place the griddle over a medium high heat until the griddle feels hot when you place your hand above it. Lightly grease the griddle. For each pancake pour 1/4 cup of batter onto the griddle and cook for 3-5 minutes until bubbles appear on the surface and undersides are brown. Adjust the heat if pancakes brown too fast. Turn over and cook a further 1-2 minutes to brown the second side. Makes 8 pancakes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix boiling water and salt.
Pour over oatmeal; let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add oatmeal. Sift together flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add nuts; mix altogether.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: In a 2 quart saucepan cook onions in margarine until tender. Add milk and cream cheese.
Stir over medium heat until cream cheese is melted.
Add the remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Makes 5 one cup servings.

title: hamburger fluffs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover bowl. Let stand in refrigerator for a few hours. Form into balls and brown in cooking oil.
Do not overcrowd. The secret of the fluffy texture is in waiting.

title: mother's french toast
directions: Beat eggs and milk with a fork in a shallow pan.
Spread cornflake crumbs on waxed paper.
Heat oil in a large frying pan. Dip bread in egg, then in crumbs and fry until browned and crisp on both sides.
Keep warm while frying all pieces.
Add oil to the pan as necessary.
Serve with syrup.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry glaze for pie
directions: Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool.
Add 4 tablespoons strawberries.
Mix and put in crust, then glaze with berries. Gently add Cool Whip on top.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple, including juice.
Chill until firm.
Fold whipped topping mix into gelatine mixture.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (by hand) and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes (until knife comes out clean when inserted into center).

title: white cake
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° until tested done.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare according to package.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: dill dip(for veggies)
directions: Mix at least 2 hours in advance.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Heat up pan.
Put oil in pan.
Put tortillas inside.
Panfry each side for 5 seconds.
After the tortillas are fried, get a separate pan.
Add 2 tablespoons of oil.
Add diced chiles and 1 can cream of chicken soup.
Mix well.
Cook until boiling.
Dip each tortilla in chile and put on tray.
Make one layer.
Then sprinkle onion and cheese on top.
Then add chile onto it. Continue as many layers as desired.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix jello and cream cheese thoroughly.
Gradually add boiling water, stirring constantly, until well mixed with no lumps.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 1/2-inch Pyrex dish.
Chill until firm.
Serve on crisp lettuce with dollop of mayonnaise.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix all other ingredients, then combine all ingredients into one large bowl and mix thoroughly.
Pour into a well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or you may use a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 35 minutes.

title: herbed potato skins
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Remove the skins from the potatoes in large strips with a sharp knife or a vegetable peeler, including some potato with each sliced skin.
Soak the skins in ice water for 15 minutes.
Remove; pat very dry.
Spread the pieces of skins out on a large baking sheet.
Spray them with a fine mist of olive oil; toss and spray again.
Bake the skins for 10 minutes; lightly spray both sides again.
Bake for another 5 minutes, then sprinkle with the herbs.
Return the skins to the oven; bake 5 minutes longer.
The skins are done when lightly browned and crisp.
Salt and pepper; serve immediately with malt vinegar or lemon wedges on the side.
Serves 4.

title: dottie's macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni until done.
Drain water off.
Mix with stick oleo until melted.
Pour macaroni in baking dish.
Mix beaten eggs, milk and cheese.
Pour on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: etouffee
directions: Saut onions, celery and green onions in butter until clear. Add garlic and cook a few minutes more. Stir in flour until deep brown color is made. Add tomatoes and simmer for 20 minutes. Add seasoning and cook slowly for 25 minutes more (low heat). Add seafood or chicken and cook until done.

title: caramel pecan rolls
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle half of pecans, dry pudding and rolls.
Repeat; melt margarine and mix in brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour over rolls.
Cover with towel and let rise overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert immediately on plate.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together with mixer and use as a dip for fruit pieces.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and flour.
Add eggs (one at a time). Add milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: french fried potato balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into deep, hot fat (390°).
Fry until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: pecan upside-down coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix pecans, corn syrup and margarine in ungreased pan (9 x 1 1/2-inches).
Spread to cover the bottom of the pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; beat 30 seconds. Spread over pecan mixture. Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: quick eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Spread slices (both sides) with mayo.
Dredge in mixture of crumbs and cheese on both sides.
Bake in a single layer in an ungreased pan at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.
Serve as is, or with your favorite sauce.
(Turn with spatula at halfway mark if desired.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine crisco and sugar. Blend in egg and vanilla, add the other ingredients, stir well. Then add chips. Put on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: t.k.'s broccoli bread
directions: Mix and pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until springs back at touch.

title: mock chicken pie
directions: Combine ingredients gently.
Season with salt and pepper. Pour into greased, 2-quart casserole.
Heat in oven until mixture bubbles.
Then cover immediately with biscuit dough.
Bake at once in 450° oven for 20 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix ingredients for 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 2 minutes. Pour glaze over cake.

title: refrigerator yeast rolls("parker house")
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Pour 3/4 cup boiling water over butter and sugar.
Add well beaten egg and stir until butter is melted.
Let stand until lukewarm, then add yeast mixture.

title: refrigerator-roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in all ingredients except 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes. Place in a greased bowl.
Turn greased side up.
Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
No longer than 5 days.
Punch down dough and divide into equal parts for whatever you are making.

title: chicken and chinese noodle soup
directions: In medium heat, stir-fry garlic until brown in oil.
Set aside.
Add chicken and broth.
While waiting for broth to boil, soak noodles for
2 minutes and cut in half.
Add the noodles and the spices until cooked.
Add celery and simmer for 2 minutes.

title: breakfast puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine flour, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and baking powder; set aside.
Using electric mixer at medium speed in medium size bowl, combine 3 tablespoons of sugar, margarine and egg.
Beat until creamy.
Alternate flour mixture and milk until combined.
Stir in walnuts.
Drop onto nonstick baking sheet into 12 equal mounds, about 2 inches apart.
Brush with melted butter.
Combine remaining 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon and sprinkle over puffs.
Bake until puffed and golden, 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Serves 12.
Contains 112 calories, 5 gm fat and 91 mg sodium.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix together hot pepper,

bell pepper (seeds too), sugar and white vinegar. Bring to slow boil and boil for 10 minutes. Add food coloring and Certo. Boil for 5 additional minutes. Strain mixture to remove seeds. Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach in cold water and remove stem ends.
Slice mushrooms and eggs.
Chop green onions, including tops.
Crumble bacon into small pieces.
Toss together and cover with Parmesan cheese.
Before serving, add Italian dressing for light coating. Serve chilled.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, soup, mayo and onion together.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with crushed Ritz cracker and melted butter.
Cook until brown.

title: onion smothered chicken(diabetic recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken into milk, then coat with flour.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet; cook chicken in oil over medium heat until browned on both sides.
Arrange chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add remaining oil to skillet; cook and stir onions until tender.
Stir in soy sauce, teriyaki sauce and water; heat to boiling.
Pour over chicken.
Cover tightly; bake at 350° until fork-tender, about 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken breasts diana
directions: Place chicken halves between sheet of wax paper.
Pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil and margarine in skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Do not overcook.
Add chives, lime juice, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth. Add remaining margarine and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken. Serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Put cabbage, onion and pepper in large bowl.
Heat the oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetables and chill.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.
(I used red bell pepper for color.)

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit juices (2 cups) with pudding.
Cook until thickened. Cool.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Broil ribs until brown on all sides.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Combine all other ingredients and place in Dutch oven. Push ribs into mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours. Make sure that all liquid does not dry up.
Add more broth if necessary. Serves 6 to 8.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: In skillet, saute meat and onions.
Add salt and pepper. Brown.
Put Pam in large casserole dish.
Lay cabbage, then meat and pour tomatoes evenly over ingredients.
Spread rice over this and add water evenly over all.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Can use 1/2 head cabbage, if desired.

title: shrimp bruschetta
directions: Combine the shrimp, cheese, tomatoes, spinach, scallions, garlic and oregano in a medium-sized bowl and stir to mix well. Set aside.

title: date nut cake
directions: Mix diced dates, soda and boiling water together.
Cream together sugar, Crisco, eggs and vanilla.
Add date mixture.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: turtles
directions: Melt chocolate squares in melted oleo and set aside.
Then mix eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Add chocolate mixture to this. Drop by teaspoons on regular waffle iron.
Bake about 1 minute on medium heat.
Frost with chocolate icing.
Makes about 24 cookies.

title: monterey burgers(good for sugar busters and atkins)
directions: In a bowl, combine meat, onion, BBQ sauce, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Form into 4 patties.
Press 1/4 of cheese into center of each patty.
Pull sides of patty up and over cheese, enclosing cheese completely.
Gently reform into 1/2 inch thick patties. Cook over medium heat 10 to 12 minutes, turning once.
Serves 4.

title: king's ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken; remove bone and cut into bite size pieces. Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle crushed chips over bottom. Add all other ingredients in order listed ending with sliced cheese on top.
Bake at 325°.
Cover and bake 20 minutes, then uncover and cook 20 minutes.
(Cooking time 40 minutes.)

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg
white
until	peaks
form.
Gradually
mix in brown sugar,
vanilla
extract and cinnamon.
Dip pecan halves individually into mixture and place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake 30 minutes at	250°.
Turn
oven
off	and let sit for 30 minutes with oven door closed.

title: mayonnaise drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat together all ingredients.
Drop in muffin tins.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 3-quart saucepan, brown meat; drain. Add spaghetti sauce and water; simmer about 10 minutes.
In bowl, stir together Ricotta, half the Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour 1 cup of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 baking dish.
Arrange 3 uncooked pasta pieces lengthwise over sauce; cover with 1 cup sauce.
Spread half of the cheese filling over sauce.
Repeat layers of lasagna, sauce and filling.
Top with a layer of lasagna and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 more minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pour apple pie filling onto ungreased baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, butter and rolled oats.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: watermelon pops
directions: You will need 8 (3 ounce) cold drink cups and 8 wooden sticks.

title: spicy hash brown potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes the night before and cool in refrigerator. Peel, if desired.
Dice potatoes.
Mix seasonings, garlic, paprika and potatoes.
Shake well in a plastic bag.
Put potatoes and onion in hot oil and fry until brown and crispy.

title: trifle
directions: Boil half cup of milk with the half & half milk.
Add sugar to boiling milk.
Add custard powder to the milk.
Cook mixture on low heat until custard forms.
Let the custard cool down.

title: spoon bread
directions: Pour boiling water over cornmeal.
Add shortening and then milk.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Bake in small shallow pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: man's favorite cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend with an electric mixer at low speed until ingredients are blended.
Turn mixer up to medium and continue mixing until smooth, scraping the sides of the bowl.
Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake 35 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: "english" yorkshire pudding
directions: Beat eggs, add salt, milk and water and beat.
Beat in flour gradually so there will be no lumps.
Use an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan, grease pan with 1 rounded tablespoon of Crisco.
(Heat pan first.)
Bake at 450° for 1/2 hour or until browned and puffed up. Serve with beef, chicken, turkey or pork and gravy.
You can also use pancake syrup on it, if you prefer.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix the cake mix, margarine and 1 egg and put in pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients well and spread over cake mixture. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: 6 week pickles
directions: You can use cucumbers, bell peppers or sweet banana peppers. Sweet banana is real good or you can mix them.
Wash and slice them.
Fill a gallon jug full.
Shake them down.
Put pickling salt, pickling spices and alum tied up in a cloth.
Put in jug and fill with vinegar and seal.
Count 6 weeks and write the date on lid.
When ready, drain off vinegar and fill with water and drain off twice.
Pour out in pan and add sugar and let stand 3 or 4 hours.
Then fill jars with the pickles; cover with syrup and seal.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil, water, margarine and oil.
Pour over dry ingredients and beat until creamy.
Add milk, soda and eggs; beat again.
Pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet (approximately 17 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch).
Bake at 400° for 16 to 18 minutes.
Ice with Chocolate Icing.

title: quick banana muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into muffin cups.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, orange sherbet and ice cream in large mixing bowl; beat until well blended.
Pour into punch bowl; gently stir in ginger ale.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: easy marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables.
Mix salad oil, sugar, vinegar, salt, water and pepper and pour mixture over vegetables.
Mix well and marinate for 24 hours.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies. Combine butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended. Beat egg into creamed mixture. Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Mix into creamed mixture just until well blended. Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart onto greased baking sheet. Bake one baking sheet at a time at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet. Remove cookies to foil to cool completely.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then flour.
In 12-inch skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Add soup mix with water; place lemons on chicken.
Bring to boil.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: oven roasted chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°. Place chicken in a lightly greased pan. Place garlic in chicken cavity. Sprinkle cavity and outside of chicken evenly with salt and pepper. Pour chicken broth over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 400° until meat thermometer registers 180° (about 55 to 60 minutes), basting often with broth. Remove chicken to a serving plate, reserving drippings. Remove garlic from chicken and mash. Pour drippings through a wire mesh strainer into a 2-cup liquid measure cup. Add enough water to measure 2 cups. Pour into a medium saucepan. Whisk in mashed garlic and gravy mix. Bring mixture to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly, 10 minutes or until thickened. Serve over chicken. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix 2 eggs, 1 stick of butter and cake mix together.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Mix 2 eggs, 1 stick butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Spread on top of first layer. Cook mixture for 1 hour at 350° or until middle sinks.
Let cool. Cut into squares and store in refrigerator.
May add pecans, if desired.

title: baked pumpkin slices
directions: Wash the pumpkin thoroughly.
Clean out the seeds.
Cut into slices.
Lightly oil a large baking pan, arrange pumpkin slices on the pan, smear oil on each slice of pumpkin, salt it and bake for 1 hour 30 minutes at 350°F.

title: christmas cherry cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions, using a greased 13 X 9 X 2 inch baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Cool cake and poke holes in it with a meat fork. Gradually pour gelatin over cake. Cool for 15 minutes then cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes. In a mixing bowl beat cream cheese until light. Fold in whipped topping and carefully spread over cake. Top with the pie filling and refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving. You may
add chopped pecans on top.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Bring zucchini to simmer stage.
Cook for 15 minutes alone, stirring frequently.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple and boil for 10 more minutes.
Add jello and cook until all jello is dissolved.
Pour in sterilized jars and seal.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour and both sugars; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter, then stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into pie shell. Bake for 1 hour.
Makes 1 pie.

title: easy curried rice
directions: Cook Uncle Ben's Instant Rice as directed but add the curry to the water.
When you turn off the heat and add the rice (as directed on the box), stir in the golden raisins at the same time. Let sit for 5 minutes.
Add sliced almonds as you serve.

title: annette's meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place all ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Roll into medium-size balls.
Place oil in large pan and place meatballs in single layer.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, browning on each side.
Serve with your favorite sauce and pasta. Makes 12 to 14 meatballs.

title: chili taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off fat.
Stir in taco seasoning, can of tomatoes, kidney beans and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
For each serving, place generous handful of taco flavored corn chips on a plate or bowl.
Top with hot chili mixture.
Garnish with shredded lettuce, grated cheese, chopped tomatoes, etc.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine in medium saucepan over low to medium heat, stirring constantly, sugar, flour, milk and egg yolks.
Cook until thick about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add vanilla and cool in mixing bowl. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar.
Add sugar slowly until thick, bold peaks form.
Layer banana slices over vanilla wafers, then pudding mixture and end with meringue.
Brown in oven.

title: chicken 'n gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in a 14 x 20-inch Reynold's oven bag.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add gravy mix, garlic powder and water.
Squeeze bag to blend ingredients. Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt and pepper.
Place in a bag.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: In saucepan, mix vinegar and ketchup, water, onion, garlic, salt, pepper, Worcestershire, hot pepper sauce and brown sugar. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour over pork chops in a deep bowl; cool.
Let stand in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
When ready to cook, arrange chops in shallow baking dish or roasting pan.
Add the sauce.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours or until chops are tender, basting occasionally with the sauce.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: almond rice pilaf
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion and almonds in butter until the onion is tender and the almonds are lightly browned.
Add broth; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and cover.
Remove from the heat. Let stand for 5 - 8 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed. Yield:
6 servings.

title: lemon barbecue chicken
directions: Season chicken with paprika and pepper.
Combine lemon juice and honey; set aside 2 tablespoons.
Broil chicken 4 to 5 inches from heat for 15 minutes, basting occasionally with lemon-honey mixture.
Turn pieces over, baste and broil 15 minutes longer, or until tender.
Combine sesame seed and reserved lemon-honey mixture.
Spoon over chicken.
Serve.
May be cooked on charcoal grill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into a heavy saucepan and boil 1 minute. Stir in peanut butter until melted.
Pour over dry ingredients, then mix together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper before mixture cools.

title: rainbow fruit
directions: Cut fruit into bite sizes; dip in jello powder for a tangy new taste.

title: snoopy snack candy
directions: Melt chips on low heat.
When melted, stir in peanut butter, nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet. Refrigerate until firm.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Pour cake mix on top.
Melt butter and pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy apple crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 11-inch baking dish with Pam.
Layer crushed pineapple in juice, then apple pie filling. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Add dry cake mix to cover apple mixture.
Top with melted margarine. Bake 1 hour.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix jello
and	water.	Cool and add remaining ingredients and pour into jello mold and chill.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese with juices, then add the rest.
Fold cream in last.
Should set for 24 hours.

title: oriental cheese ball
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese, pineapple, pepper, onion and salt. Mix well.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Makes 2 balls. For dip, thin out with pineapple juice.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Wash and rinse lettuce.
Tear into bite size pieces.
Chop and dice the bell pepper after removing seeds.
Add dried tomatoes. In separate bowl, combine oil and vinegar, then mustard.
Add black pepper.
Toss salad with dressing and add croutons.

title: no crust zucchini quiche
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Mix all ingredients with a fork and pour into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: snow peas with water chestnuts
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart glass casserole, heat oil 15 seconds.
Add water chestnuts and snow peas.
In a 1-cup glass measure, heat water 2 minutes.
Dissolve bouillon cube and add to vegetable mixture.
Cook vegetables, covered, 4 to 6 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking time.
Combine cornstarch and cold water; mix well.
Push vegetables to one side of casserole and stir cornstarch mixture into broth.
Stir vegetables into sauce.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes, stirring every minute, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Salt to taste.
Yields 4 servings.

title: old fashioned macaroons
directions: Blend coconut, sugar and egg whites in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 10 minutes.
Remove and stir in extract.

title: little pizzas
directions: Split muffins and spread sauce on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put toppings on pizza.
Put under broiler or microwave on High until cheese melts.

title: cereal nut krunch
directions: Melt butter in 4-quart heavy aluminum pan or roaster.
Add sauce and salts.
Blend thoroughly.
Add cereals, pretzels and nuts.
Stir carefully.
Place in slow oven (250°).
Bake for 1 hour, stirring carefully every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven. Serve hot or cold.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 7.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine milk and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour.

title: six-layer cookies
directions: In a 7 x 9-inch pan, melt butter.
Spread evenly in pan the graham crackers, flaked coconut, chocolate bits, condensed milk and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into small squares.

title: lemon delight
directions: Chill milk 2 or 3 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Whip milk until thick.
Add sugar and lemon juice; beat until thick. Layer mixture in bottom of bowl.
Place wafers on top.
Repeat until all is used.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: cream cheese blintzes
directions: Stir together milk, flour, eggs, 1 tablespoon margarine, sugar and salt; beat until smooth.
Let stand 30 minutes.
For each blintz, pour 1/4 cup batter on hot, lightly greased skillet.
Cook on one side only until lightly brown.
Spread browned side with sour cream and roll up.
Before serving, brown in remaining butter.
Top with raspberries and sour cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lazy lady cake
