directions: Spread pie filling and pineapple in 13 x 9-inch pan (glass). Sprinkle dry cake mix, coconut and nuts over filling.
Pour melted butter all over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool well and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peanut bars
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat flour, sugar, butter and salt until mixture resembles coarse crumbs, press firmly and evenly into pan.
Prebake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in raisins, carrots, coconut and pecans. In separate bowl, combine eggs, oil, apple and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir only until combined.
Spoon into greased or paper-lined muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Makes about 18 muffins.

title: potato-onion casserole
directions: Quantity of Potatoes and Onions depends on the sizes of either one.

title: old-fashioned pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Gradually add sugar to softened shortening and beat until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Stir the flour, mace, cream of tartar and salt together.
Add a little at a time to creamed mixture, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Bake 1 hour.

title: life in throop recipe
directions: Mix thoroughly and add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy for others.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and add faith.
After pouring all into your daily life, bake well and serve with a smile.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: Place chicken breasts in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over it.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 minutes.
Place rice, vegetables and 1/2 can onions around and under chicken.

title: eggplant gourmet style
directions: Cut eggplant
into
8 parts lengthwise and fry in olive oil until brown
and
tender,
about 10 minutes for each part. Place tomato
sauce in casserole.
Add eggplant; sprinkle well with cheese.
Dot with butter and bake in moderate oven (375°) 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together.
Add orange juice.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: mom's marinated carrots
directions: Add the rest of the ingredients to the cooked carrots and marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: miami beach cake
directions: Melt 1/3 cup morsels. Grease and flour bottoms of two 9-inch layer pans. Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Stir in walnuts and 2/3 cup morsels. Set aside.
Combine flour with soda and salt. Cream butter.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar and cream well. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Blend in melted morsels and vanilla.
At low speed, add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Turn into pans.
Sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool.
Beat cream with 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff. Fill and frost sides, keeping layers top side up.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach dip(reduced calorie or regular)
directions: Combine all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill (overnight if minced onion used).
Makes 3 cups.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream the butter.
Add grated cheese, salt and red pepper. Sift together flour and baking powder. Add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Mixture will be stiff and short.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: santa claus cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon 1/4 cup batter into each cone and place filled cones in muffin pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack.

title: turkey and carrot patties
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together shredded carrot, water and minced dried onion.
Cover with clear plastic wrap; vent by leaving a small area unsealed at the edge of the bowl.
Microcook on High about 1 1/2 minutes or until the carrot is tender.
Drain.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Pare turnips and chop onion. Boil in small amount of water until tender, then mash. Add 2 cans soup, sour cream and carrot. Add about 2 cups stuffing mix (seasoned). Pour into casserole dish; dot with oleo and sprinkle some stuffing on top. Bake in 350° oven about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit pie filling cake
directions: Pour oil in 9 x 13 pan and spread. Add cake mix, eggs and water. Blend with a fork. Spread evenly. Add pie filling on top and marble. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double broiler over simmering water. Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat and blend in condensed milk and peanuts.
Drop by tsp. on baking sheet.
Cool at room temperature 2-3 hours.
Store in a air-tight container.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, flour and nuts and use enough milk to help make it spread.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time. Sift flour into mixture. Add nuts and vanilla. Bake at 325° in 8 x 12 Pyrex dish for 35 minutes or until firm.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: In bowl combine chicken, soup, mixed vegetables and stir. Pour into greased 9 X 9 pan spread evenly. Add biscuits on top of mixture. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water and then add 1 teaspoon sugar. In a 3-quart bowl, add 1/3 cup sugar, shortening, egg, salt and 1 cup warm water.
Beat thoroughly and add dissolved yeast. Gradually beat flour into mixture.
Mix and knead with hands until dough becomes stiff to beat.
Place covered in a warm place and let rise until double in size, about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Press down and place in refrigerator.
On the day you wish to bake, roll and shape as many rolls as desired.
Do this in early afternoon and allow rolls to stand in cool place.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour nuts evenly in bottom.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over nuts in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: tasty little devils
directions: Cut eggs in half (lengthwise).
Scoop out yolks in small mixing bowl and mash with fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon yolk mixture into egg white halves.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: grandma's crumbcake
directions: Blend sugars, flour and shortening together.
Set aside 1 cup of this mixture.
This will be your topping.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: Mix lemon and orange jello with hot water and add cold water after jello is fully melted.
Let begin to set and add remaining ingredients and chill well.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt butter and add to dry ingredients. Beat eggs and vanilla.
Add to mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in sprayed pie pan in 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: sweet-sour cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrot if not using "shredded cabbage packages".
Add diced onion and put in a large bowl.
In a medium saucepan, add vinegar, oil, sugar and all above listed spices. Stir.
Bring to a boil and pour over cabbage.
This recipe is great when made one day in advance.

title: sausage soup
directions: Brown sausage in saucepan.
Add other ingredients; cook twenty minutes.
Place in bowl with Parmesan cheese on top.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Crumble crackers; pour in sweet milk and let soak in.
Cream margarine and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir crackers and milk mixture to make sure they are soft.
Add cracker mixture and baking powder to butter and sugar mixture.
Add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into four 9-inch pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into cooled cooked pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Chill and serve.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and salt; beat.
Add Karo syrup, vanilla and butter.
Beat all together.
Put pecans in bottom of unbaked pie crust.
Pour filling mixture over pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk, pinch salt in top of double boiler. Let cool and add creme de cocoa and creme de menthe slowly. Whip cream and fold into mixture.
This fills 9-inch chocolate crumb pie crust.
Keep in refrigerator.
It can be frozen.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions, celery and salt in water until tender. Add pepper, milk and margarine and bring almost to a boil. Serve hot.
When in the bowl, sprinkle crumbled crisp bacon on top.
If desired, you can use shredded cheese also.

title: swedish meat balls(serves 100)
directions: Heat oven to 350°; have meat ground together.
Crush or run bread cubes through blender.
Beat eggs slightly and sprinkle over other ingredients and mix well.
Form in meat balls.
Easy way to brown these is put one layer deep on cookie sheet with sides and brown them.
Put in baking casserole; add 1 1/2 quarts water and 3 or 4 cans mushroom soup.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter.
Cook until boiling.
Then add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Spoon out onto wax paper and let stand for approximately 10 minutes.

title: dave's sho'nuf sketty sauce
directions: Brown hamburger in a skillet.
Drain; set aside.
Clean and cut up vegetables; set aside.
Mix tomato paste with 2 cans of water each in a bowl.
Empty stewed tomatoes in a bowl and cut up. Now mix paste, stewed tomatoes and spaghetti sauce in a large pot with a lid on high heat.
Add vegies and stir in.
Add spices to taste.
Bring to a boil, then a simmer and add meat; stir.
Let simmer for 45 minutes to an hour.
Add seasonings to taste if necessary.
Add water to desired consistency.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: cocoa drink
directions: Mix well.
Use 1/3 cup milk to 1 cup of boiling water.
This makes a little more than a gallon of dry mix.

title: casserole potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes
in skins until tender.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.	Peel
and
grate.
Add	other above ingredients. Place in
greased
casserole dish.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Microwave rice, water and salt on High for 15 minutes.

title: quick walnut penuche
directions: In saucepan, melt butter over medium-low heat.
Stir in brown sugar.
Cook and stir over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add milk; bring to boiling.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat in powdered sugar until like fudge.
Stir in walnuts.

title: party mints
directions: In an electric mixer, cream the cream cheese.
Blend in powdered sugar, a little at a time, to make a stiff dough. Continue to knead dough by hand.
Pinch off enough dough to fill mold.
Roll in granulated sugar and press firmly into mold.
Pop out of mold.
Makes approximately 75 mints.

title: 90 minute pretzels
directions: Mix one cup flour with the sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat 1 cup water and margarine.
Gradually add to the dry ingredients and beat for 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough. Knead 5 minutes.
Set in a greased bowl.
Cover.
Let rise 40 minutes.

title: red pepper relish
directions: Chop or dice peppers and onions.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: angel food cake
directions: Let eggs stand at room temperature an hour before using.
Use an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Start the oven for moderate heat. Sift flour once before measuring.
Measure and add 1/2 cup sugar. Sift together 4 times.
Combine egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and flavorings in large bowl.
Beat with flat wire whip until the whites form soft peaks, but are still moist and glossy.
Then add rest of sugar in 4 additions by sprinkling about 5 tablespoons at a time over whites and beating until sugar is blended, about 25 beating strokes each time.
Add flour and sugar mixture in 4 additions, sifting it over egg whites.
Fold in each addition with flat wire whip, turning bowl gradually.
Use 15 complete fold over strokes each time.
After last addition, use 10 to 20 additional fold-over strokes.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven, invert pan on cake rack and let stand 1 hour, or until the cake is cool.
Then loosen from sides and around tube with a slender knife, gently drawing out cake.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until a ball forms.
Remove from heat and drop on wax paper. After cooling, knead and store in airtight container.

title: pork chops and dressing
directions: Brown pork chops, if desired.
Arrange chops in an 8 or 9-inch square baking dish (glass).
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Turn chops over after 5 minutes.
Drain and save juices.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, onion, mayonnaise and cheese together.
Chip the butter in mixture.
Cover with cracker crumbs and bake.

title: instant pumpkin pie
directions: Add spices to dry pudding mix.
Then add milk; mix slowly with beater until just blended (30 seconds).
Blend in pumpkin and 2 cups whipped topping.

title: chicken with lemon sauce
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Combine 1/4 cup flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Add chicken pieces, a few at a time, shaking to coat.
Cook chicken in hot margarine or butter in large skillet over medium-high heat 8 to 10 minutes or until tender and no longer pink, turning once.
(Reduce heat as necessary during cooking to prevent over browning.)
Remove from skillet, reserving any drippings.
Keep warm.
For sauce, combine both and 3 tablespoons flour in screw-top jar.
Cover and shake well; add to skillet.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Stir in lemon juice and sugar; heat through. Serve sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with chives.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl and microwave for 2 minutes. Stop and mix well, then microwave approximately 1 minute.
Serve hot with crackers.
Easy!

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add dressing just before serving.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolates.
Using rounded teaspoonfuls, shape into balls.
Roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from oven and top with candy Kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash, dry and split pickles.
Combine vinegar, water, sugar and spices.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pack pickles in jars, then pour boiling liquid over top.
Put a little dill on top of each jar. Process 10 to 12 minutes or water bath.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling water 6 to 7 minutes.
Drain.
Put eggplant, onion and croutons in baking dish.
Mix soup, milk and egg; pour over eggplant.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Put the green tomatoes, peppers, cabbage and onions through the food chopper.
Add the salt.
Let stand overnight; drain.
Mix with the syrup, vinegar, mustard seed and turmeric.
Boil 20 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Combine V-8 juice, meat, onions, seasonings and 6 cups water. Cover; simmer for 2 hours.
Cut meat from bone in large cubes. Skim off excess fat.
Add meat and vegetables; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add cabbage and noodles last 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in margarine in skillet until tender.
Spoon into pie shell.
Sprinkle with Swiss cheese.

title: james smith pie
directions: Melt
butter, add flour and pecans. Press in baking dish. Bake until done. Let cool.

title: egg custard
directions: Cream flour, sugar and eggs together, then add buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg to taste.
Mix well, then pour in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix cottage cheese, dry Jell-O, pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix well and mold or put in bowl and garnish with chopped pecans.
This is very good with Triscuit wafers or Town House crackers.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Bake in greased mini muffin tins at 450° for about 15 minutes or until lightly brown. Makes 24 rolls.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Blend sugar and soft butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Sift flour.
Add a cup at a time and beat well. Add Crisco oil; beat well.
Add 7-Up and lemon.
Beat.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until cake is done.
Before removing cake from pan, glaze.

title: baked squash
directions: Simmer squash in salted water until tender; drain.
Place squash and cream cheese in casserole.
Mash cheese and squash together; add garlic salt.
Mix well.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: tuna noodle crisp
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Melt shortening in large skillet; add onion and
green
pepper
and
cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, pimento,
salt
and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add cooked noodles and flaked	tuna.
Mix well and put in 1 1/2 or 2 quart casserole.	Sprinkle
with	bread
crumbs
and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix wafer crumbs, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar together and pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese and 1 1/2 cups sugar together on high until creamy.
Add the vanilla and rum.
Blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and the melted chocolate.
After well blended, add the chocolate chips.
Pour over wafer crumb crust.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° until top cracks. Let cool 10 minutes.
Mix sour cream with 1/2 cup sugar and pour over top of cake, covering completely.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.
Decorate by drizzling chocolate syrup over top.
Garnish with strawberries or raspberries.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Layer a well-greased 3-quart casserole.

Begin with tortillas, chicken, sprinkle chili powder and garlic salt, follow with half of the soups mixed with the broth, bell pepper, onion and cheese. Begin second layer with tortillas and the rest of the ingredients. Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Cover during half of the baking time. Serves 8.

title: oven fried chicken wings
directions: In 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch roasting pan in 425° oven, melt butter.
Remove pan from oven.
On wax paper, mix next 5 ingredients.
Pour buttermilk into small bowl.
Dip one wing at a time in buttermilk, then in crumb mixture.
Place wings in melted butter in roasting pan, turning to coat evenly.
Bake 35 minutes or until chicken wings are tender.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with a mixer until smooth.
Spread with a spatula on a pizza pan.
Top (in order) with lettuce, onion, tomato and Cheddar cheese.
Use nacho chips to scoop and eat!

title: praline crunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans. Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine all crunch ingredients until crumbly.
Divide into 3 portions.
Press 1/3 of the mixture into the bottom of each of the prepared pans.

title: chocolate macaroon bars
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Beat in egg, vanilla, salt and soda.
Stir in the flour, chips and coconut.
Spread in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cut into bars or squares when cooled.

title: nana's brownies
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine the flour and sugar.
In a heavy saucepan combine butter, shortening, coffee and cocoa.
Stir and heat to boiling.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites, then add the pineapple and pecans. Pour in 10-inch tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: chili con carne y frijoles
directions: Soak beans in bowl overnight; drain.
Place beans, onion, and salt pork in large saucepan with water to cover.
Simmer, covered for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients in a very large bowl.
Add margarine, eggs and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Pour in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
This mix can be kept in tight container in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.

title: apple slices
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Cut lard in with pastry blender.
Put egg yolk in measuring cup and add milk to make 2/3 cup; add to lard mixture.
Mix just enough so dough shapes into ball.
Roll out 1/2 of dough to 15 x 11-inch rectangle.
Transfer to baking sheet.
Cover with corn flakes, then apple slices.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Roll out other half of dough for top crust.
Pinch edges together.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Put on top.
Bake in a 400° oven for 40 minutes.
While hot, dribble glaze over top.

title: black bean dip
directions: In food processor, combine beans and garlic and process, using on-off motion, until smooth (do not puree). Transfer to bowl and stir in salsa.
May also use a blender.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage in skillet and drain.
Thaw bread dough.
Roll out in rectangle form and coat with melted butter or oleo.
Put a layer of browned sausage, olives and cheeses.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese. Fold sides up and ends over and seal bread.
Bake on greased pan at 300° until brown; approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This makes 3 large loaves.
They can be refrigerated or frozen until needed.

title: doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large mixing bowl, combine hot milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix eggs and mashed potatoes into yeast mixture.
Add flour and stir. Knead on lightly floured surface for 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Roll dough out until about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Place on lightly floured surface, cover and let double in bulk.
Cook in deep hot oil, turning once, each side being golden brown.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut and boil potatoes.
Boil eggs; peel and cut.
Cut apple and onion real fine.
Mix potatoes, eggs, onion, relish, pickles, apple, mayo, mustard, salt and pepper.
Put parsley and paprika on top.

title: hot lettuce dressing
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Stir in vinegar, cornstarch and water. Cook until thick.
Add crumbled bacon to dressing.
Pour dressing over lettuce right before serving.

title: sauerkraut bake
directions: In large
skillet fry bacon until crisp, drain on paper towel and
crumble.
Set
aside.
Add onion to drippings, cook until lightly
brown
and
tender.
Drain
on paper towel.
In large bowl
combine
tomatoes, kraut, sugar, bacon and onion. Turn sauerkraut mixture into a 2-quart casserole and cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350° and bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple and carrot cake
directions: Mix in large
bowl
eggs, salad oil and sugar.	Add and stir in	grated	carrots,
pineapple,
vanilla and nuts.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Blend into carrot and
pineapple mixture.
Turn into ungreased pan. Bake at 350° until
center
springs
back
when	touched,
40 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook onions and pepper in skillet until tender. Combine in bowl with chicken and chilies. Set aside. In the same skillet, melt 3 tablespoons butter. Blend in flour, coriander and salt. Stir in chicken broth all at once; cook and stir until thick. Remove from heat; stir in sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese. Cut up tortillas (or use chips) and mix together. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven about 25 minutes. Serves 6. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: oriental salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower & broccoli into small chunks.
Combine cauliflower, broccoli, mushrooms, water chestnuts and onions.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, milk, sour cream and chilies together.
Dip tortillas in hot grease to soften, but can use as is.
Put a small amount of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put chicken (as much as desired), cheese and a spoonful of mixture in tortilla.
Roll and place in pan.
Add extra mixture and cheese to top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: andrew's zap-it s'mores
directions: Spread Marshmallow Fluff or place marshmallows between two graham crackers.
Add chocolate chips to taste.
Put in microwave until marshmallow is soft and warm.

title: squash stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until just softened, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add yellow squash and zucchini; cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, about 8 minutes.
Stir in parsley, white wine, oregano, salt and red pepper flakes.
Cook, stirring, until mixture is heated through, 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, butter, cocoa and milk for 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Beat well and hurry.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: toasted mushroom rolls
directions: Chop mushrooms	and
saute
for
minutes
in butter. Blend in flour,
salt
and
Accent; stir in cream.
Cook until thick; add
chives
and
lemon juice.
Remove crust from bread and roll thin
with rolling pin.
Spread with mixture and roll up.
Pack and
when
ready to serve, cut each roll in half and toast on all sides at 400°.
Serve immediately.	These can be frozen, defrosted and toasted when ready.

title: old fashioned corn pudding
directions: Blend honey or syrup and milk.
Add flour gradually, stirring until smooth.
Add eggs, corn, butter and salt; mix well.
Turn into greased 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with allspice.
Place baking dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes until custard is set.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Mix 1/2 can soup, beef, crumbs, egg, onion and salt.
Shape in an 8 x 4-inch loaf.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
In saucepan, blend rest of soup and water and add 2 to 3 tablespoons of drippings.
Heat.
Pour over loaf and bake 15 more minutes.

title: herb baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Parboil just until tender. Melt butter in saucepan.
Add paprika, salt, Italian seasoning, garlic powder and barbecue spice.
Mix well.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Melt butter in large fryer. Salt and pepper chicken and fry in butter until lightly brown. Place chicken in baking dish. Pour out half of batter that is left.
Add cream of chicken soup to remaining butter and stir together, mixing in the crumbs in the fryer. Pour this mixture over chicken pieces. Cover and bake 1 hour or until tender at 375°.
Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: mediterranean coffee
directions: Measure 4 cups of freshly boiled hot water.
Add 4 level teaspoons of Nescafe instant coffee.
Stir vigorously 5 seconds. Pour immediately into four ready cups and serve.
Serves 4. Repeat process for coffee addicts (or double ingredients).

title: battered herb fish
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Roll fish in melted butter, then crumb mixture.
Place in pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken chip casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery, then mix all the ingredients.
Place in ungreased casserole dish. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, beat sugar and butter until creamy.
Beat in egg until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chopped chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned.
Let stand on cookie sheet 2 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: oat bran date bread
directions: Mix oat bran, dates, dry milk, molasses, hot water, butter and egg substitute in large bowl. Stir in remaining ingredients. Spread 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pan and let cool completely before slicing.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers fine; add melted butter. Mix well and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: congealed cranberry salad #1
directions: Bring water and pineapple juice to boil. Add lemon jello. Mix with cranberry sauce and nuts. Refrigerate until set.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Soften Hershey bars over
hot water until they are limp (not runny) and
soften
butter.
Cream
butter and chocolate; add eggs.
Mix dry
ingredients.
Mix
some
flour
with nuts. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to the creamed mixture; add nuts.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 70 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add bananas, pineapple and strawberries.
Put half in refrigerator until set.
Put sour cream on top of set jello.
Pour other half on sour cream and place in refrigerator.
Put Cool Whip on servings.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and beat well. Add baking soda to buttermilk; stir until it foams.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add flour and 2 teaspoons vanilla (optional).
Add baking powder.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Bake about 25 minutes at 425°.

title: coconut cake
directions: Boil sugar and water for 1 minute; add flavoring.
Pour over cake while still in pan.
Let stand for 1/2 hour (sprinkle a little powdered sugar on top to keep it from sticking to plate).
Turn out on plate and immediately turn back on another plate so it will cool right side up.

title: delicate garden lettuce
directions: Rub a large wooden bowl with cut sides of garlic.
Add oil, lemon juice and salt to bowl; stir well.
Add lettuce; gently toss.
Chill 30 minutes before serving.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: heather's favorite chicken casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, tear or cut chicken into bite size chunks.
Stir in sour cream, soup, bread crumbs and broth. (Bread crumbs and broth can be omitted.)
Adapt amount of broth and bread crumbs, judging by consistency; should be moist and smooth, not runny or stiff.
Top with cracker crumbs, melted or grated butter and poppy seed.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 25 minutes.

title: carolin's texas chili
directions: In a small saucepan, cook onion, pepper and celery in 1/4 cup water until tender.

title: grandma wagner's squash bread
directions: Mix in order.
Pour into buttered loaf pans. Bake at 350° to 375° for about 70 minutes.
Yields 3 large loaves.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 inch glass baking dish.
Spread hash browns in dish; sprinkle with sausage.
In a bowl, beat eggs and milk together.
Add salt, dry mustard and cheese; mix well.
Pour egg mixture over sausage. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted into center comes out clean. Serves 6 - 8.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Prepare dough as directed on package.
Roll out and bake for two minutes.
Meantime scramble six eggs.
Pour on the pizza dough.
Garnish with bacon bits, grated cheese, diced onion, diced peppers and whatever fits your fancy.
Bake at 450 degrees for 15 minutes or until eggs are cooked.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Bake
the
cake
mix
on a cookie sheet (with sides) 15 minutes.
Mix
cream
cheese and topping, then add pudding and milk.
Spread on the cake when cool.
Add coconut and nuts.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Shake blueberries in flour and mix with rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: low-fat chicken enchiladas
directions: Filling:
(Use 1 to 2-quart saucepan.)
Saute onions in 1 to 2 tablespoons canola oil until onions are soft.
Add chicken or turkey (cut into 1-inch pieces) and cook until meat is white in color.
Season meat with chicken bouillon granules and salt and pepper to taste.
Add sour cream and enchilada sauce.
Mix well and place on very low heat to keep warm.

title: italian sausage chili
directions: Brown sausage and set aside.
In drippings, cook beef, onion, garlic, green pepper and celery until meat is done.
Add tomatoes, chili powder and chili beans.
Mix sausage in this mixture and cook until tomatoes are soft. Cook on low heat.
Garnish each serving with shredded cheese.

title: orange roughy with dill
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 12 x 8-inch or 8-inch square baking dish melt butter in oven.
Place fish fillets in baking dish; turn to coat with melted butter.
Sprinkle with dill weed, salt and pepper. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers and put in large mixing bowl.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
This salad is especially good if put in a covered plastic container and chilled for a couple of hours before serving.
Do not freeze.
Keeps well chilled for several days.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat.
Add water to cover meat.
Simmer 30 minutes, covered.
Saute peppers and onions in a little oil until soft. When meat is finished, add a few dashes of soy sauce.
You may thicken the sauce with some cornstarch, if desired.
Combine meat and gravy with the cooked rice.

title: diabetic strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Slice strawberries and sweeten with 15 packets of Equal. Add strawberries, pineapple and nuts to Jell-O mixture and 1 cup cold water.
Pour half of this into a 10 x 10-inch bowl and put in freezer to set fast (do not let freeze). Add 5 envelopes Equal to sour cream and spread over jelled mixture.
Pour remaining Jell-O on top and refrigerate.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: baked lima beans in tomato sauce
directions: In large saucepan, combine the beans and 7 cups of water; bring to boiling.
Boil gently 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, 1 hour.
Bring beans to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered 30 minutes or until beans are just tender.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup of cooking liquid.
Cut 6 slices of bacon in 1/2-inch pieces.
Saute lightly in medium skillet.
Add onion and saute until onion is tender and bacon is browned.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: "super good dessert"
directions: Bake cake according to directions on 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix eggs as a custard.
Add to the corn. Shake crumbs over top.
Add butter and salt and pepper to taste.

title: ed's stuff
directions: Cut chicken breasts into bite sized pieces. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet. Cook chicken until done. Pour picante sauce into hot skillet and cook uncovered 2 to 3 minutes to thicken. Place tortilla chips on a microwave safe plate, spoon chicken mixture on chips, sprinkle with cheeses. Heat in microwave on high for 30 seconds or until cheese is melted.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onions and seasonings.
Mixture will be thick.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes, stirring often.

title: corn relish(serving size: 4)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; then combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Toss them.
Chill for 2 hours.
Makes 4 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Grease small casserole with margarine.
Mix first 8 ingredients together and pour into casserole.

title: tropical beverage
directions: Put in blender for 4 minutes.
Chill and serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, corn syrup, eggs and evaporated milk.
Stir butter into hot milk.
Combine brown sugar, salt and spices.
Mix until well blended.
Combine all 3 mixtures.
Pour into pie shell.

title: easy skillet supper
directions: Cut bacon into 1/2-inch pieces.
Place in large skillet and pan-fry until crisp.
Add ground beef and onion slices; cook until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Cut potatoes and green pepper in julienne strips; reserve.
Stir soy sauce and water into hot meat mixture.
Add prepared vegetables; mix thoroughly.
Cover and cook over high flame until steam escapes.
Then turn to simmer and cook 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, 1/2 cup melted margarine, eggs, sugar and vanilla together in mixing bowl.
Pour into buttered casserole. Mix remaining ingredients with 1/3 cup margarine.
Sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: filled cookies
directions: Roll brown sugar.
Pour Crisco over it, then drop 1 egg at a time and beat.
Add cream of tartar, soda, salt, flour and vanilla.
Roll out and cut.
Fill with 1 teaspoon Raisin Filling, placed on top.
Crimp edges.
Bake in moderate oven until done at 350°.
Will be golden brown.

title: oven bake potatoes
directions: Wash and cut potatoes into small pieces (do not peel).
Mix flour and cheese together in plastic bag, adding potatoes.
Melt butter in shallow pan or on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, mix sugars, flour, spices and salt.
Add apples; toss lightly to combine.
Put in bottom crust.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Dot with butter.
Place top crust on the apples.
Cut vent to let steam escape.
Flute edges.
Mix yolk with 1 tablespoon water.
Brush on crust.
Bake at 425° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with Cheddar cheese or dollop of vanilla ice cream.

title: black bean soup
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, heat the olive oil over moderate heat for 1 minute; add the onion and garlic and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until the onion is soft.
Stir in the oregano, thyme, cumin and cayenne pepper and cook, stirring, for 1 minute longer.

title: crunch cookies
directions: Mix together brown sugar, white sugar and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add this to the sugar mixture and blend thoroughly.
Then fold in oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Mixture will be very stiff.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar, then sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Mix flour mixture with other ingredients and add chips.

title: creamy tarragon dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Serve as a dip for raw vegetables.

title: sausage gravy and biscuits
directions: Brown sausage, drain and set aside.
Prepare gravy as directed on package.
Mix the gravy and sausage together.
Bake biscuits as directed on package.
When biscuits are done, cut in half and pour gravy over biscuits and serve.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in crock-pot.
Let cook on low all day.
Serve with corn muffins or homemade bread.

title: coconut dessert
directions: Heat
oven
Combine the butter or margarine, flour and
coconut
in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook and stir often for
40 minutes,
until
very brown (stir about every 10 minutes).	Allow to cool, taking out 1/4 of mixture for topping. Press rest in bottom of pan.
In another bowl, mix the vanilla pudding
and milk until thick.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Spread over the mixture in the pan.
Top with the extra crumbs.

title: apple salad
directions: Toss apples,
celery, nuts and marshmallows with mayonnaise; fill lettuce cups.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix (with hand) flour, sugar and butter.
Put 1/2 cup crumbs to side.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into cake pan, then put the 1/2 cup of crumbs on top of batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine chili, beans, tomato sauce and ground beef and heat.
Layer ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer, starting with tortillas, then chili mixture and then cheese.
Keep layering and finish up with tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put pickles in jars with a slice of onion, 1 clove garlic and fresh dill.
Boil juice and pour over pickles.
Put lids and rings on jars.
Put in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes lots.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Combine first 7
ingredients and put in a boiler.
Let bubble for about 20 minutes.
Put in casserole dish. Cover with rolls and cook as directed on can.
Melt cheese and put on top of baked rolls.
Return to oven until cheese is browned.

title: savory spinach squares
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, butter, onion, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, salt, thyme and nutmeg and mix well.
Combine spinach, rice and cheese.
Add egg mixture and mix well.
Pour into a greased shallow pan, 2-quart size.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Cut in squares for serving.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: mex-italian lasagna
directions: Combine chili, salsa and mushrooms; set aside.
Combine cheeses and seasonings; set aside.
Boil noodles according to box directions.
Starting with chili mixture, then noodles, then cheese, layer 3 times.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Blend or beat until smooth.
Serve in chilled glasses. Garnish with orange slice or pineapple spears.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line the bottom of 9 x 13 inch casserole dish with the crescent rolls (spread them out and press seams together).
Top with browned sausage and then with cheese.
Combine the eggs and milk.
Pour over the top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes at 425 degrees or until golden brown.
Cool before serving.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 9x13-inch baking pan and put a slice of Swiss cheese over each breast.
Mix the sherry and soup together and pour over the cheese covered breasts.
Crumble the herb stuffing evenly over the chicken and cheese.
Drizzle the melted butter over the stuffing.
Bake at 350°, uncovered for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (depending on the size of the chicken breasts).

title: zebra brownies
directions: In a small bowl, beat together the filling ingredients until smooth. Set aside.

title: lemon frosting
directions: Cut margarine into sugar.
Add lemon rind.
Add lemon juice a little at a time until spreadable consistency.

title: holly candy
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in double boiler (or microwave). Add vanilla and food coloring, stir until blended.
Pour over cornflakes and stir until well cooled.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper, sprinkle with teaberry candy.
Let dry overnight.
Makes 100 pieces.

title: colonel punch
directions: Chill all ingredients for 1 hour.
Pour in soda and champagne last, then add ice.
Add cherries, lemons and orange slices for decorations.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Line bottom of punch bowl with crumbled cake.
Add a layer of each of the following:
pudding and fruit, ending with pudding. Top with Cool Whip, coconut, pecans and cherries.

title: stuffed vienna bread
directions: Score bread by slicing lengthwise to within 1/2-inch from bottom in 1-inch sections.
Turn and do the same in the other direction.
Stuff bread sections with cheese and mushrooms. Sprinkle onions, poppy seed and seasoned salt over top.
Melt butter; add lemon juice and dry mustard.
Stir to dissolve. Gently spoon butter mixture over bread.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
To serve, fold foil back.
Guests help themselves by pulling pieces off with a fork.

title: cheese 'n chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion and margarine in large skillet until tender.
Stir in chicken, 1/4 cup picante, cream cheese and cumin; cook until thoroughly heated.
Stir in 1 cup cheese.
Spoon about 1/3 cup chicken mixture into center of each tortilla; roll up.
Place seam side down in 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining picante sauce and cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: In a bowl, whisk together mayonnaise, anchovies, onion, shallot, tarragon, parsley, chives and vinegar.
Taste and add salt, if needed.
Makes a generous cup.

title: german coffee cake
directions: Spread on cake batter top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or light brown.
Test with toothpick, done if comes out clean.

title: kahlua dessert
directions: To make first layer, mix cake mix, Kahlua, oil and eggs.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix
together
cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, chives and Worcestershire sauce;
form
into a ball.
Press ball into the pecans and
roll
to
keep shape.
Refrigerate before serving. Serve on any type crackers.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate until firm.
Can serve on lettuce leaf.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Mix liquid smoke, soy sauce, consomme, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and barbecue sauce. Cover brisket with this mixture and marinate overnight. Bake in same liquid, covered, basting occasionally, in preheated 225° oven 6 to 8 hours.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Place all of the above in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for 24 hours.
I remove the roast from the pot after 12 hours or more and cut or pull the beef apart, then return it to the pot and allow to simmer for a few more hours.
This makes wonderful sandwiches.

title: saucy baked beans
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine pork and beans, onion, pepper, brown sugar, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Top with bacon. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy stir-fry
directions: *May use 1/2 cup currant jelly instead.

title: tom's favorite chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and garlic.
Add salt and pepper. Add tomatoes, beans, tomato juice and chili powder.
Bring to boil, then simmer covered for 30 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: date balls
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients for 6 minutes, then add chopped pecans.
Cool and roll into balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: foo foo
directions: First, peel bananas or strawberries, and put them in the bowl. Mash the bananas or, cut the strawberries into small pieces.
Add pecans.
Second, add the 1 cup of flour and stir.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 of cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 of onion rings.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake 5 minutes longer, uncovered.
Vegetables will be crunchy.
For more well done, precook according to package directions.

title: squash casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients.
Top with sliced cheese and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; add soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Mix well; add apples and nuts.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: low-fat garlic croutons
directions: Sprinkle bread with garlic powder on both sides. Put on a cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray or use a rack to put bread on.
Bake in 300° oven until bread is dry and crispy, about 25 minutes.
Turn bread halfway to get both sides dry. Break in pieces and keep in airtight container until ready for use.

title: frozen tropical punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender except ginger ale.
Freeze. Put in punch bowl and pour ginger ale on top when ready to serve.

title: never fail pie crust(makes 3 crusts)
directions: Sift together flour, salt and shortening.
Add egg, cold water and vinegar.
Mix together well.
Make 3 balls.
Roll out.
Place in 9-inch pie pan.
Makes 3 crusts.

title: french onion soup
directions: Place water and beef cubes in a pan; stir and bring to a boil. Saute in a pan the onions and butter for 1/2 hour, then pour into water and beef cube pan.
Serve in onion soup bowls.
Top with croutons and Mozzarella cheese.
Place in oven on broil until cheese is brown.
Excellent!

title: marinated carrots
directions: Put carrots in bowl.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over carrots, stir and make sure all carrots are covered.
Refrigerate. Will keep up to 10 days.

title: rice and sausage casserole
directions: Combine cooked sausage with remaining ingredients.
Put into a greased casserole and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix together above ingredients until well blended, cover top with mini marshmallows - let congeal.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower in small pieces. Cream the cheese and mayonnaise together. Add other ingredients and stir well. Chill overnight.

title: cranberry fruit nut bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Combine peels, juice and egg.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just to moisten.
Fold in berries and nuts.
Turn into greased pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine lemon juice, sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Add to berries and toss.
Add butter; beat egg yolk and water. Brush top and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: nut roll
directions: In a large bowl, combine crushed vanilla wafers, raisins and chopped pecans.
In another bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Pour Eagle Brand milk/lemon juice mixture over dry ingredients and mix well.
Shape into a loaf or roll.
Wrap tightly in waxed paper or foil.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Slice thin and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and spread in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt sarah's lemon curd(english recipe)
directions: Beat the eggs in the top of a double boiler. Stir in remaining ingredients and cook over simmering water about 30 minutes, stirring frequently until thick and smooth. Lemon curd will thicken more when cooled. Cool, cover and refrigerate. Spoon into 1-cup crocks or jars. Cover with plastic wrap and tie with ribbon. Keep 2 to 3 weeks in the refrigerator. I use lemon curd to fill tarts or on toast or scones.

title: oatmeal banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Add bananas to mixture. Add flour and oats.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Mix all together.
Put in crock-pot for 6 hours on low.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble when cool.
Fry onion in bacon fat.
Add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add potatoes and simmer until needed.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine and pour into greased or buttered loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: dieter's cornbread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and stir well.
Add beaten egg and buttermilk; stir until smooth.
Pour batter into a 9-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 9 servings; 120 calories per serving.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Layer coconut flakes and pecans in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix together powdered sugar, butter and cream cheese.
With tablespoon, spoon over cake mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: diet cheese cake
directions: Drain pineapple juice and put in a bowl.
Mix with gelatin and set aside.
In blender, put eggs, pineapple, cottage cheese, Sweet 'N Low and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add juice mixture.
Will be like pancake batter.
Spray pan with Pam.
Pour batter into pan.
When done, place frozen blueberries on top.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Good with hot chili.

title: barbecue sauerkraut
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: corn pudding or blender corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in scalded milk.
Add flour, salt, sugar, vanilla and pepper to beaten eggs.
Add this to milk and add corn.
Mix well.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar, cream of tartar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Combine egg and milk.
Add to flour all at once, stirring just enough to stick together.
Turn onto lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly 15 times.
Roll to 1-inch thickness.
Cut and place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 16 biscuits.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix first
4 ingredients together.
Pour into casserole with tight fitting
cover or cover with foil.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of rice.
Pour sherry over chicken (if sherry is omitted, replace with
1 cup milk, water or chicken bouillon). Top with dry onion soup	and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: dijon chicken
directions: In frying pan, lightly brown chicken in oil.
Take out; put to the side.
Cover chicken with some of the mustard; coat with bread crumbs.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches in a casserole dish.
Pour cake mix on top. Slice butter stick and lay on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Combine cherry pie filling and lemon juice; spoon into lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Combine flour, brown sugar and cinnamon; cut in butter, until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in oats. Sprinkle mixture over pie filling.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 24 minutes.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Note:
To sour milk; to 1 cup sweet milk, mix 1 tablespoon vinegar or lemon juice.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a 2 cup glass measuring cup.
Stir in water, cook in microwave full power 1-1/2 minutes Stir 2-3 times. Blend in butter and cook 30 seconds.
Add vanilla and stir thoroughly.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken; chill thoroughly and bone.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Grease 2-quart casserole; lay broccoli in bottom and put chicken on top.
Combine next 4 ingredients and pour over (can be put in fridge for 24 hours if desired).
Before baking, sprinkle with cheese and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: baked apple pudding
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and egg in mixer bowl.
Heat until light.
Gradually blend in combined flour, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Stir in vanilla, apples and walnuts.
Turn mixture into an ungreased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until done.
Serve warm or cold, topped with whipped topping or ice cream.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: tomato-basil sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients except oil in blender at high speed. Add oil and blend until will emulsified.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Grease casserole or baking dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in casserole at 375°
for 1 hour.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.

title: stir-fry vegetables and rice
directions: Bring water and rice to a boil. Simmer for 20 minutes. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet. Add carrots and stir-fry 2 minutes. Add 2 onions, green peppers and garlic. Stir-fry 2 minutes more. Add oil if needed. Add mushrooms, pea pods and cooked rice. Cook 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in soy sauce and serve.

title: little smokies
directions: Mix together and heat in pot.
Add little smokies and heat. (I usually make a double batch and put them in a crock pot)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients. Dissolve the soda in the water.
Add to mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: low-fat honey coke barbecue chicken
directions: Take off skin and fat from chicken.
Mix other ingredients. Cut chicken in pieces.
Put in big saucepan and add ingredients. Do not add water.
Cook in open pot over medium heat about 1 1/2 hours, until sauce has cooked down.
Remove and place in oven in shallow pan and let brown lightly.
Serves 4 people.

title: surprise sausage n' eggs
directions: Combine sausage, oats, egg and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Divide meat mixture into four parts and shape each part around a hard-cooked egg.
Place egg on a rack in a shallow baking pan. Bake in a preheated 375° oven about 35 minutes or until sausage is cooked.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour half of the mixture into a greased 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of this.
Pour in rest of mixture and top with more cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: pretzel salad
directions: In a bowl, combine, pretzels, sugar, and margarine, set aside 1/2 cup for topping. Press the remaining mixture in an ungreased 13X9 pan. In a mixing bowl, beat whipped topping mix, milk and vanilla on high speed for 4 minutes, or until soft peaks form. Add creamed cheese and confectioners sugar; beat until smooth. Spread half over crust. Top with pie filling and then with remaining cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle reserved pretzel mixture over top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick. Put in an unbaked pie shell and bake until firm and crust is brown. When cool, add meringue and bake until peaks are brown.

title: minced clam dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften at room temperature. Drain juice from clams. Blend garlic, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce with cream cheese.
Mix in minced clams, then juice. Season with salt.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix the milk and soup together and pour over the chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Put cracker mixture over top of chicken and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; put into large bread pan.
Lay chicken on top, skin side down.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken, skin side up.
Take foil off and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: one dish village chicken
directions: Cook the rice as directed on package, but stop cooking 3 minutes earlier than instructed so rice mixture will not become dry.
Spread the rice on the bottom of a lightly oiled 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place the chicken breasts on top of the rice.
Cover chicken with cheese, then sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 325° oven for 25 minutes or until chicken is done and bread crumbs are slightly brown and crisp.
If desired, melted butter may be added part-way through the baking process to add crispness to the bread crumbs.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: angel hair with tomatoes, basil and garlic
directions: Prepare pasta according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, heat oil in a skillet.
Add garlic and cook for 1 minute. Add tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper.
Cook for 3 minutes. Add hot pasta to skillet; toss well.
Add chicken broth and stir. Toss with Parmesan cheese and serve immediately.

title: haystacks
directions: In a saucepan, put butterscotch morsels.
Heat over low heat until morsels are melted.
Add peanuts and noodles to mixture. Stir until well coated.
Drop mix by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Cool.

title: light rolls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add boiling water and allow to cool slightly.
Beat egg into yeast and water.
Add to creamed margarine (which has cooled enough not to kill yeast). Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Let rise until doubles (approximately 1 hour). Batter will be sticky; don't add extra flour.

title: zucchini rounds
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and stir until mixture is moistened.
Fold in zucchini.

title: potato lasagna
directions: Press broccoli between paper towels until barely moist. Combine broccoli, Ricotta cheese and next 4 ingredients in a medium bowl; stir well.
Set aside.
Coat an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Place 1/3 of potato slices in bottom of dish.
Spread half of broccoli mixture; sprinkle with half of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers and top with remaining potato slices and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 55 minutes or until potato is tender and top is golden.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yield:
8 servings (194 calories per serving).

title: caribbean cheese enchiladas
directions: Roll tortillas with chicken and cheese.
Place seam side down in 9 x 12-inch pan. Melt margarine. Add flour and stir. Add the chicken broth, sour cream, cream of mushroom soup and chilies. Pour over tortillas.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat.
Take 10 (8-inch) flour tortillas; place 2 tablespoons mixture in center.
Roll up and place in 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Top with tons of shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: waldorf astoria cake(red cake)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat.
Add food coloring and vanilla; beat.
Add buttermilk and beat well.
Add all dry ingredients and beat well.
Add soda to vinegar.
Last, fold in soda and vinegar.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Spread over meat loaf and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut round steak in serving size pieces.
Place in crock-pot. Pour tomatoes, pepper and onion over steak.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low for 8 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix cornbread mix and eggs together well.
Add chopped onion. Rinse and chop head of broccoli.
Fold into the mixture.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan and top with grated cheese.
Melt stick of margarine and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until cornbread is done.

title: cheesy garlic bread
directions: Slice French bread into 1-inch slices.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Spread butter mixture between bread slices and on top and sides of loaf.
Wrap loaf in foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.

title: fruit and cream cake
directions: Grease and flour an 8-inch spring-form pan.
In blender, puree 1/3 of the fruit.
Add water to make 1/2 cup.
Stir together flour, soda and salt.
In mixer bowl, beat eggs on high 4 minutes. Gradually add sugar and beat 4 to 5 minutes on medium until sugar dissolves.
Gradually add flour mixture and beat until combined. Heat puree and butter until melts.
Add to batter and mix until combined.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.
In mixer bowl, beat whipped cream and powdered sugar until soft peaks form.
Cut cake horizontally.
Spread with half of the cream and half of the fruit on first layer.
Repeat with top.
Heat jam and 1 tablespoon water. Cool slightly, then drizzle over top.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: In microwave, melt 14 ounces almond bark and entire bag of chocolate chips in large bowl until mixture is smooth, stirring every 1 to 2 minutes. Add cereal, marshmallows, pecans and raisins to melted mixture. Stir until well coated. Immediately pour onto wax paper-lined pizza pan to make one large pizza or spoon onto wax paper to make individual servings. Top with M&M's. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: upside-down sausage pie
directions: Cut or shape sausage into patties.
Placed in an unheated skillet.
Cook over low heat until patties are well browned.
Pour off excess fat as it accumulates.
Be sure patties are well cooked and place in casserole dish.
Brown the onion rings in a small amount of sausage drippings.
Place fried onions over sausage patties in casserole dish and add undiluted tomato soup.
Sift all dry ingredients in a mixing bowl; blend in margarine.
Add milk to make a soft, but not sticky, dough.
Turn onto a floured board and pat out to size that fits casserole dish.
Place on top of meat mixture.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Biscuit dough should be well browned and done throughout.
Place on platter so that meat mixture is on top.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: old-fashioned pumpkin fudge
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, pumpkin, condensed milk, pumpkin spice and salt in a saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat; cook to 238° on a candy thermometer (soft ball stage), stirring occasionally.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Parboil asparagus.
Remove crusts from bread slices.
Flatten bread with rolling pin.
Soften cheeses and mix with softened butter.
Spread mixture on bread slices.
Place asparagus on each bread slice.
Roll up and brush or dip in melted butter.
Cut each roll into 3 pieces and freeze.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 375° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix margarine and cream cheese until creamy.
Add sugar and mix for 3 minutes with mixer.
Add eggs and flavorings.
Mix well.
Gradually add flour until well blended.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until pick comes out clean.

title: mexican candy
directions: Pour sugar and milk in a pan; mix and cook until it is hard when dropped in water.
Add nuts.
Cook a minute longer.
Add vanilla.
Then drop by spoonfuls on a sheet of waxed paper.

title: chocolate peanut butter cups
directions: Line muffin pan with paper cups.
In a medium bowl, stir together the peanut butter, corn syrup and vanilla, until blended. Gradually stir in the sugar.
Turn out onto a smooth surface; knead until smooth.
Press with hands or use a rolling pin to make 1/2-inch thick.
With 1-inch cookie cutter, cut into 1-inch rounds.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop vegetables, then put boiling water over it and let set for 10 minutes. Drain.
Pour 1 part vinegar and 2 parts water over this and bring to a boil.
Drain again. Combine remaining ingredients and cook all together (with vegetables) for 15 minutes.
Can and seal.
Good on hot dogs and hamburgs.
Yields 6 1/2 pints.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir eggs, syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.

title: molded waldorf salad
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin in bowl; stir until gelatin is dissolved.	Stir in orange segments (with syrup), pineapple (with syrup), apple and banana.
Pour into 5 cup mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
6-8 servings.

title: sharon's triple layer mud pie
directions: Pour chocolate and sweetened condensed milk into large bowl. Stir until smooth. Add pecans. Pour into crust. Refrigerate 10 minutes. Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes or until smooth. (Mixture will be thick.) Spread 1 1/2 cups of the pudding over chocolate in crust. Immediately stir 1/2 of the whipped cream topping into remaining pudding. Spread over pudding in crust. Top with the remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate for 3 hours or until set.

title: almond torte
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Mix the pudding with milk.
Blend in cream cheese (slightly softened in microwave). Spread mixture over cooled cake.
Drain pineapple and spread over pudding mixture.
Spread layer of Cool Whip.
Top with almonds.

title: blueberry ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients except blueberries and refrigerate for a few hours or overnight.
When ready to make ice cream, put blueberries in blender or food processor and puree.
Should be about 4 cups.
Pour cream mixture into ice cream freezer container and process according to freezer instructions.
Ice cream will be a deep blue.

title: cantonese chicken in black bean garlic sauce
directions: Combine black bean garlic sauce, oyster sauce and sugar and set aside. Heat oil in skillet over medium heat and saute garlic until light brown, about 2 minutes. Stir in red and green peppers, white onions and green onions. Cook until white onions start to turn translucent, 1 minute. Add chicken and cook until no longer pink, stirring occasionally, about 3 to 4 minutes. Add black bean garlic sauce mixture and pepper and mix well. Cook until chicken is cooked through, about 3 to 4 minutes more. Garnish with chopped green onions. Serves 3 to 4.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Fill large pan with water and chicken.
Cook and debone; add to water and spaghetti and cook until done.
Add sour cream and soups and cheese; cook until cheese is melted.
Pour into large casserole dish and bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: christmas holly cookies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows; add coloring and vanilla.
Pour over the corn flakes; mix well.
Drop on waxed paper about a teaspoon at a time.
Add red decorations to resemble a Christmas wreath.
Quite pretty.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter until well creamed.
Add beaten eggs. Slowly add flour, vanilla and milk.
Beat at high speed until mixed well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until brown on top, about 5 minutes.
You should put foil on edges of crusts to keep them from browning too fast.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Put butter in 8-inch baking pan and melt.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Dip cut side in butter, then press into cheese. Place cheese side up until cooked, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel and slice peaches; set aside.
Put margarine in a baking pan and let melt in oven.
Combine flour, sugar and milk.
Mix until thin batter is formed.

title: red lobster rolls
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.
Mix melted butter and garlic and brush on rolls.

title: sweet story cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Combine milk and cherry juice, then add 3/4 cup (save balance for later).
Add flavorings.
Beat 2 minutes on low speed, or 200 strokes by hand.
Add remaining liquids and egg whites. Beat 2 minutes more.
Blend in nuts and cherries.
Bake in 2 layer pans in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with cherry frosting mix.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and toss with stuffing.
Place 1/2 of stuffing on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place boned chicken on top of stuffing.
Pour 1 cup broth over stuffing and chicken.
Combine soup, sour cream and 1/2 cup broth.
Spread mixture over top of stuffing and chicken.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over top, along with slivered almonds, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: turkey meat loaves
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl and shape into 4 small loaves.
Arrange around the edge of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes.
Remove to a plate and spoon ketchup on top and microwave for 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters.
Combine cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and butter.
Sprinkle 1/3 in buttered casserole.
Cover with a layer of oysters.
Repeat layer.
Add Worcestershire sauce to milk. Pour over contents of dish.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top. Bake in moderate oven at 450° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: angel macaroons(makes 6 dozen)
directions: Blend cake mix, water and extract and beat 30 seconds on low speed.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed, then fold in coconut.
Drop by scant teaspoonfuls 3 inches apart on a cookie sheet that has been lined with foil, then greased.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Chill thoroughly before removing from foil.

title: ma hayter's fruitcake
directions: This is a no bake fruitcake.
Chop or cut all nuts, candy and figs into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients by hand in a large bowl.
Use just enough juice to make the cake stick together and to moisten the cracker crumbs.

title: wild rice turkey dish
directions: Cook rice mix.
Add soup; add next 6 ingredients and 1 cup water; mix well.
Put into 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet milk griddle cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place 1/2 cup or 3/4 cup batter on a greased pan.
Depends on how thick you want your pancakes.
Cook over medium-high heat.

title: chicken or crab casserole
directions: Cook artichoke or use canned.
In small bowl, blend flour, milk, broth, salt and pepper.
Melt butter and saute onion and mushrooms until tender.
Pour in milk mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in sherry and half of the cheese.
Place artichokes in bottom of greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugars, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture. Add nuts. Pour into two greased loaf pans or make muffins. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: spiced apples
directions: Cook candies, sugar and water together.
When candies are melted, simmer about 12 wedges at a time
until they are transparent.
Transfer to a bowl and continue until all apples are done.
Pour syrup over the apples and chill.

title: congealed vegetable salad
directions: Boil water, vinegar, salt and sugar.
Pour over jello.
Drain remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: crock-pot beef roast
directions: Cook roast until almost done.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook until done, low 10 to 12 hours, high 5 to 6 hours.

title: praline pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Grease and flour a 10 inch tube pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans in the pan.
Set aside. Cream butter or margarine and cream cheese.
Add brown sugar and cream, until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Fold in flour until just combined. Do not over mix.
Stir in vanilla and remaining 1 cup chopped pecans.
Spoon batter into prepared pan and place on a baking sheet in the oven.
Bake for 1/2 hours or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove to rack to cool completely.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add one egg at a time and beat 2 minutes after each addition.
Add coconut extract and add buttermilk, flour, baking powder and salt alternately.
Stir in coconut and put in greased and floured tube pan (not Bundt pan). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked beans(in a crock-pot)
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Put beans in crock and take pork out of the beans; add all remaining ingredients.
Heat on high until warmed through (or until bubbly); reduce to low and simmer until desired thickness.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Pour gelatin into cold water; set aside.
Chop the green pepper, onion and celery.
Put undiluted tomato soup into a pan. Add the cream cheese, stirring constantly until cheese is blended into the soup.
Set aside and cool.
Cut up shrimp and oil mold. Add gelatin to soup; mix together.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well; add to mold.
Refrigerate until molded and ready to use.

title: #1 fudge
directions: Put butter in a large glass bowl; microwave on High for 1 minute, or until melted.
Add sugar, cocoa, milk and vanilla; stir until well blended and smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Press into an 8-inch square dish; refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares and enjoy!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat potatoes until smooth.
Add margarine, seasonings and eggs.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until slightly brown on top in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter and add brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each.
Fold in flour and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Place in oblong cake pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and All Bran cereal.
Add soda to this and set aside to cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add buttermilk to sugar mixture.
Sift flour into bowl, saving 1/2 cup to flour nuts.
Add salt and 40% Bran Flakes to flour.

title: green tomato sweet relish
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add vegetables, a few at a time.
Process until ground.
Transfer to a large nonaluminum bowl; sprinkle with pickling salt and let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Drain well.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, spices and salt.
Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Add molasses and blend.
Sift together twice flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to molasses mixture and stir until blended.
Chill well.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Using a floured rolling pin, roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness on floured pastry cloth or board.
Use cookie cutter to press out desired shapes.
Place on greased baking sheets and bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 30.

title: peanut peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In saucepan, combine peanut butter, brown sugar, butter or margarine and lemon juice.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Add undrained peaches, cutting up any large pieces. Immediately turn hot peach mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cookie dough pieces.
Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream.
Makes 9 servings.

title: cheesy vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Layer half the onions in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with Parmesan cheese, half the Ritz crumbs, half the cheese cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers, beginning with remaining onions.
Spread with mushroom soup; sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, then more Parmesan.
Garnish with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab salad
directions: Pick over crab meat for shells.
Toss all ingredients thoroughly with enough mayonnaise to make mixture of a potato salad consistency.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in shortening until softened.
Add bananas and half of buttermilk; mix until flour is damp.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add rest of buttermilk and eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Add nuts and stir.
Bake in greased or paper-lined pans at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
It may be topped with whipped cream and sliced bananas.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and lemon extract.
Fold in 7-Up.
Pour in a well-greased floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pat's fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and seed apples.
Squeeze lemon juice over them; set aside.
In large bowl, combine sugar, eggs and oil.
Mix well until smooth.
Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder. Add to sugar mixture.
Fold in and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
