Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: sugar cookie i
directions: Cream sugars, eggs and butter.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Drop teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Flatten with spatula dipped in water.
Sprinkle with white sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350°.

title: turkey vegetable medley
directions: In large pan sprayed with Pam, cook turkey until broken apart and browned.
Add all other ingredients including liquid from canned vegetables.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 425° for approximately 20 minutes or until done.

title: peanut clusters
directions: In large saucepan, heat sugar, butter and milk to boiling, stirring constantly.
Cook for 3 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat; mix in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oatmeal and peanuts.
Drop mixture by tablespoon onto waxed paper (if mixture becomes stiff stir in one or two drops of milk).
Let stand to firm.

title: raisin nut pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: mom's potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Blend butter and flour and gradually add milk.
Stir until boiling; cook until thickened.
Stir constantly.
Add 2/3 of the cubed cheese.
When melted, pour over cooked macaroni in greased casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes (20 minutes covered and 10 minutes uncovered).

title: skillet hash
directions: Combine beef, potatoes, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Melt shortening in large skillet over medium heat.
Spread meat mixture in skillet.
Brown hash 10 to 15 minutes; turning frequently with a wide spatula.
Stir in water.
Reduce heat; cover and cook for 10 minutes or until crisp.

title: cappuccino milk shakes
directions: Pour coffee, brown sugar and hot water into a blender and cover.
Blend until coffee is dissolved.
Add cocoa powder, cinnamon, ice cream and milk.
Cover.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, sugar, melted butter and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
"Do not overbake!"
Sprinkle powdered sugar in pan and roll baked cookies in powdered sugar and set aside to cool.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Make jello with only half the water called for on the box. Mash cranberry sauce and add to hot jello mix.
Add pineapple, grapes (quartered) and nuts.
You can use whatever grapes and nuts you wish.

title: shrimp and feta cheese with mostaccioli
directions: Wash and pat shrimp dry.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Saute green onions and garlic in oil in a large skillet until tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in chopped tomatoes, wine, salt, pepper, basil and 1 tablespoon parsley.
Lower heat; simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until mixture thickens slightly; stir in shrimp and lemon juice; cook over medium heat just until shrimp turn pink and feel firm, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add cheese and sprinkle with remaining parsley.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg and sugar together until very smooth.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and apples.
Bake in greased Pyrex pie plate in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping or vanilla ice cream.
Serves 4. Double recipe for more servings.

title: chocolate velvet cake
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and 1/4 cup water.
Stir over low heat until melted (cool).
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Cream sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Blend chocolate in mixture.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with 1 cup water.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peach dumplings
directions: Wash peaches.
Take flour.
Add pinch of salt, then mix in potato water until mixture is consistency of pie dough.
Roll out dough until large enough to fit around peach.
Wrap dough around peach.
Pinch together at top.
Cook in boiling water until peach is tender and dough well done.
Stir frequently.
Top with cinnamon, butter and sugar.

title: italian cheese ball
directions: Cream ingredients together and form ball.
Roll ball in parsley flakes or finely chopped nuts.
Remove from refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Shape dough into small rolls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Frost cake.

title: norwegian honey cake
directions: Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour over raisins in a bowl.
Toss to coat.
Sift together the remaining flour, baking soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Beat eggs and sugar in a bowl until fluffy.
Beat in sour cream and honey.
Stir in flour mixture just until blended. Add raisins and orange rind.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch angel tube pan.
Bake in preheated slow oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake pulls away from the sides and the top springs back when lightly pressed.

title: gramma's potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Layer mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes. Casserole is finished when chips are slightly browned.

title: egg-drop soup
directions: Heat broth to boiling point in large saucepan.
Meanwhile, in small bowl, make a smooth paste of cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water.
Into hot broth, slowly stir cornstarch mixture with sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; mixture should be slightly thickened and translucent.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Heat the broth to a boil.
Add pork, ginger root, and black mushrooms.
Cook for about 3 minutes.
Remove ginger root.
Add remaining ingredients except cornstarch, water, eggs, and green onions.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Combine cornstarch with the water and stir until blended.
Add to soup mixture and cook until thickened and clear.
Remove from heat and slowly stir in beaten eggs.
Garnish with green onions.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for twenty-five minutes or until a fork inserted in the filling comes out clean.

title: tomato dip for raw vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with raw vegetables.

title: asparagus and ham spaghetti sauce
directions: Melt butter and olive oil in electric frypan.
Add onion, diced ham and asparagus.
Saute.
Add water and chicken bouillon cube and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cream and Parmesan cheese.
Toss around.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.

title: golden summer punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 7 minutes.
Then add pineapple, orange, and lemon juices.
Freeze until slushy.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: chili
directions: Simmering is the secret of this recipe.

title: cheese dip
directions: Dip with tortilla chips.

title: date pudding
directions: Cut up 1 1/2 cups of dates and 1 cup of nuts.
Soak 1/2 cup dates in boiling water.
Let stand while you mix:

title: frank's best sweet potatoes
directions: Use a big pot.
Add all ingredients together.
Cook for 1 hour on a medium stove.
Keep mixing until done.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, corn oil and eggs.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add to mixture, then add the water.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 to 3 loaves.

title: round steak roll
directions: Put mustard on pieces of steak; salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Put slice of bread on steak and roll up; secure with toothpicks.
Brown and then add a little water and cook slowly for about 30 minutes.
Good served with a vegetable and salad.

title: turkey wild rice casserole
directions: Place turkey, mushrooms, carrot, broccoli and sherry in saucepan.
Cover and heat over medium heat, 3 to 5 minutes or until turkey is hot.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole; keep hot.
In same saucepan, prepare rice according to directions.
Stir in turkey mixture and Swiss cheese.
Return to casserole and place in preheated 350° oven for 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese melts. Remove from oven; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and top with green onions.
Serve at once or keep warm in a 200° oven until ready to serve.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pecan pie cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients, except pecans, and pour over top of crust. Sprinkle pecans on and bake for an additional 30 minutes or until firm.

title: soup de jour
directions: Lightly saute onion and peppers in a large pot.
Add soup mix and water and cook for awhile.
Add leftovers from refrigerator and freezer.
Let it simmer for a while.
Taste seasoning; add herbs. Add water as needed or V-8 juice.
Add noodles near end of cooking. A little white wine or dry sherry or a teaspoon or so of red wine vinegar might be nice.

title: oven potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, then cut or dice.
Mix onion soup mix and olive oil together in small bowl.
Put in potatoes.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour, or until golden brown, in baking dish.

title: magic meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes in a large bowl.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in crock-pot.
Place potatoes at the sides of loaf.
Cover and cook on low 10 hours.

title: crunchy salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces. Break broccoli into small florets. (You may steam broccoli but keep it crunchy.) Chop onions with tops. Slice mushrooms. Crush noodles before removing from package. Saut almonds, noodles and sunflower kernels in margarine. Set this aside to cool.

title: snowball candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips with milk over low heat; stir in powdered sugar.
Chill; form into balls.
Roll in Angel Flake coconut.

title: chicken sunday dinner casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice evenly over bottom of well-greased pan.
Heat the soups with the milk, stirring until well blended.
Pour over rice.

title: creamed sweet cabbage - pink cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage coarsely.
Put in large pot; barely cover with water.
Add salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer until cabbage is tender.
Chop the onion; cook in the margarine until tender and golden brown.
Add the flour, stirring continuously, until the mixture is light brown.
Add this to the cabbage, stirring to dissolve.
Cook until the liquid in the pot thickens.
Remove from heat; stir in the sour cream.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Boil white sugar and white syrup together 5 minutes.
Add peanut butter, margarine and vanilla.
Pour over corn flakes. Drop by tablespoons on waxed paper.
Cool a little, then shape in balls or cookies.

title: icing for jam cake
directions: Put 1/2 cup of the sugar in iron skillet over low heat.
In sauce pan, mix remaining 2 cups of sugar, milk, butter, and egg. Stir mixture over low heat until butter melts then increase heat and boil rapidly.
Take sugar that is in iron skillet melted and pour in other mixture.
Stir fast and constantly.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add 1 tsp. vanilla.
Beat well and spread on cake.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger; put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add Tater Tots, followed by frozen vegetables.
Mix soup, milk and garlic powder.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over soup. May top with a can of French fried onions, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more until vegetables are soft.

title: light dilled potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes in large cubes.
Put into large bowl.
Sprinkle with oil and vinegar and toss lightly to coat.
Combine all other ingredients in separate bowl and blend well.
Pour over potatoes. Toss gently to coat well. Cover and chill.
Keeps well at least 24 hours.

title: farina dumplings for soup
directions: Beat eggs; add farina.
Let stand about 10 to 15 minutes. Drop into boiling soup.
Cook 15 minutes or until tender.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan with butter.
Put a layer of whole graham crackers in the pan. Then add a layer of pudding mixture.
Alternate crackers and pudding layers.
End with crackers.
Heat the container of frosting in the microwave for about 1 minute to make it thin. Spread on top of crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: yellow rice and chicken
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil.
Debone and cut in bite-size pieces after browning, then brown onion, garlic and bell pepper. Place all in pan, meat included and brown a little more but do not burn.

title: garlic dill pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with ice water; let stand until vinegar mixture is ready.
Heat water, vinegar and salt.
Put cucumbers in jar with garlic and dill.
Pour hot mixture over cucumbers and seal.

title: bea's sour cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time.
Add flour and soda, alternating with sour cream.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour into Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter in meal and deep fry.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Marinate pork in soy sauce mixed with 1 tablespoon cornstarch for 15 to 30 minutes.
Bring stock to boil; add salt, mushrooms and bamboo shoots.
Add pork, bean curd, pepper and vinegar. Bring to a second boil and stir in 2 tablespoons cornstarch mixed with the water.
Continue to boil until pork is done and the soup is thickened.
While stirring boiling soup, slowly pour in the beaten egg.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar; add to butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk; fold in coconut and vanilla.
Pour into heavily greased and floured 9-inch pan (no crust).
Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: roast goose
directions: Season the goose inside and out with salt and pepper and stuff with apples and prunes.
Put in a large pan and brown goose on all sides in hot oven.
Add 4 cups boiling water and baste. Roast for 3 hours at 325°.
For crisp skin, pour 2 tablespoons water over the goose and let brown 15 minutes.
Skim fat from drippings.
Strain and thicken for gravy.
Serve with your favorite side dish (red cabbage is good), potatoes and a green salad.

title: cream of wild rice and chicken
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion, carrot, and celery in butter until tender.
Spoon in flour and stir.
Gradually add broth.
Stir in rice, chicken, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes until thick. Stir in milk and cook another 3 to 5 minutes until thoroughly heated.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown in skillet ground chuck, sausage, onion and seasonings. When brown, add Velveeta cheese. When cheese is melted, spoon onto party rye.

title: tuna macaroni
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on label.
Drain tuna and mix in macaroni and cheese lightly.

title: sand tarts(penna. german for christmas)
directions: Cream butter until softened.
Add sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy.
Add eggs in thirds, beating well after each addition.
Add the flour in fourths, mixing until blended after each addition.
Chill dough overnight.
Using a small amount of dough at a time, roll out to 1/16 inch thick, on lightly floured surface and cut into small 2 inch rounds or small animal shapes, trees, stars, Christmas or holiday symbols.
Brush with beaten egg white, sprinkle with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon and press a pecan piece onto center of each cookie.
Transfer to cookie sheets. Bake at 350° about 9 minutes.
Keep in airtight containers.
Yields about 7 dozen small cookies.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and cream.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in wine, spaghetti, chicken and mushrooms.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes or until bubbly.
To brown, place briefly under broiler.

title: green salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and pineapple, then other ingredients.
Transports well with minimal refrigeration.

title: pancakes
directions: I traveled many miles today,

title: fiesta jalapeno & tomato dip
directions: Microwave Velveeta, tomato and garlic powder in 2 quart microwavable bowl on high 4 to 5 minutes or until Velveeta is melted, stirring every 2 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips. Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: savory pork chops with rice
directions: Lay pork chops in 9 x 13-inch pan, put 1 tablespoon of rice on top of each pork chop, then place onion slice on top.
Combine tomato soup and brown sugar in a bowl and 1 cup of water.
Stir together until smooth, pour over pork chops.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered, and serve.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Pour hot milk over oatmeal.
Let stand 10 minutes (1/2 hour if using regular oatmeal).
Add syrup, cooking oil and beaten egg yolks.
Dry mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Beat only until smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Fill well-oiled muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375°
for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine the sliced squash and next 4 ingredients; cover with ice.
Let stand about 1 1/2 hours.
Meanwhile, combine sugar and remaining ingredients (seeds may be tied in cheesecloth bag) in pot and simmer 5 minutes.

title: garden taco rice
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except rice and cheese; bring to a boil. Stir in rice.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until liquid is absorbed, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Fluff mixture with fork; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let stand 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Garnish with cilantro and cherry tomatoes, if desired.

title: morning glory eggs
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Stir sour cream into eggs, then pour into prepared dish.
Sprinkle sausage or bacon over eggs, then cheeses.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, if desired. Bake, uncovered, at 350° until heated through and bubbly and cheeses are melted, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with salsa, garlic cheese grits, angel biscuits and fresh fruit.

title: dark cake
directions: Boil raisins in 2 cups	water for 15 minutes.
Let cool a little. Cream shortening,
sugar and egg together.	Sift dry ingredients together and add
to
raisins.	Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 35 to 40
minutes	in 2 loaf pans, 9 x 5-inch (greased and floured).

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Sift the flour with soda and add to first mixture, mixing well.
Blend in remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen cookies.
Very delicious in taste and when dropped from teaspoon and baked 10 minutes, makes a chewy cookie; baked longer makes a crisp cookie for dunking.

title: easy wine pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Brown chops in heavy skillet. Season with salt and pepper.
Add white dinner wine to half cover the meat.
Arrange quartered onions around chops and sprinkle with chopped garlic.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour or until meat is fork-tender.
Add more wine, if needed.
Serve with rice.

title: pear cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add orange juice and beat good.
Add vanilla, coconut, pears, dates and pecans.
Stir by hand.
Use tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: garden peas and asparagus
directions: Drain garden peas.
Layer on bottom of casserole. Drain asparagus.
Layer on top of peas.
Mix soup with 1/3 cup milk and pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Layer grated cheese on top.
Heat at 350° until cheese melts.

title: crowd pleasing potatoes
directions: Mix well all ingredients except corn flakes. Place in baking dish. Top with mixed corn flakes and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer. They improve with baking.

title: cranberry orange muffins(makes about 3 dozen tiny muffins)
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°. Butter small cupcake pans (1 3/4-inch top diameter and about 3/4-inch deep). If you don't have enough muffin tins, bake the muffins in relays, like cookies.

title: low fat chicken salad
directions: Mix together chicken, celery, mayonnaise, and onion powder. Serve on bread as sandwich or on greens as a salad.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas into softened cream cheese.
Spread onto tortillas and roll up.
Refrigerate.
Slice into 1-inch slices and serve with Picante sauce.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt part of diced cheese in hot macaroni; save some for top. Combine ingredients.
Cook in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Slice chicken in 1/2-inch squares.
Mix with salt, pepper, cooking wine and cornstarch; set aside.
Heat 2 tablespoons peanut oil and add salt, saute snow peas, mushrooms, celery and water chestnuts for 2 minutes.
Remove from pan and fry garlic, chicken and onion for 1 minute (on high heat).
Add soy sauce and sugar; mix well.
Add cooked vegetables.
Mix well and cook for 1 minute. Remove and serve over rice.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Place Ritz crackers on a cookie sheet; spread with tomato paste.
Top with a small slice of Mozzarella cheese and a slice of pepperoni.
Sprinkle with ground oregano.
Bake at 325°.
Great for party snacks.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in salt water.
Mash potatoes and all ingredients except butter.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and dot with butter or oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach cream freeze
directions: Combine all of the ingredients, adding Cool Whip last.
Freeze the mixture until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine egg, buttermilk, baking mix and cheese in a bowl; mix well with fork.
Pour into 2 small or 1 large loaf pan, greased. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into slices, but not through the bottom.
Spread slices apart; drizzle mixture of melted margarine and garlic salt over and between slices.
Wrap in foil. May be reheated several times.

title: chicken breasts lombardy
directions: Place each piece of chicken between
2	sheets	of
wax paper and flatten to 1/8-inch thickness,	using meat mallet or rolling pin.
Dredge chicken lightly
with
flour.
Place	4 pieces at a time in 2 tablespoons melted
butter
in
a
large skillet; cook over low heat 3 to 4
minutes
on
each
time or until golden brown.
Place chicken in greased 13
x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, overlapping edges.	Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste. Repeat procedure with
remaining
chicken, adding 2 tablespoons butter to skillet each time.
Reserve drippings in skillet. Saute mushrooms in 1/4
cup
butter
until	tender; drain. Sprinkle evenly over chicken.
Stir
wine
and chicken stock into drippings.	Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Spoon 1/3 of sauce evenly over
chicken.
Reserve
remaining	sauce. Combine cheese and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 450° for 10 to
12	minutes. Place under broiler 1
to
minutes
until lightly
brown. Serve with reserved
sauce.
Yield:
servings.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill before serving.
Cooked peas or grated carrots may be added if desired.
It is better if you fix the day before using; the flavor is better.

title: swedish brownies
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, a little at a time, beating well.
Fold in melted margarine, salt, flour and extract.
Spread into 11 x 15-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle additional sugar on top, then sliced almonds on top of sugar.
Bake in 325° oven 30 minutes.
Don't bake until brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Pour mixture into buttered baking dish.
Set in a pan of hot water 1 inch deep.
Bake at 350° until firm in center, about 30 minutes.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip, drained crushed pineapple, pudding mix and marshmallows together.
Spread in dessert dish.
Then add Maraschino Cherries to top.
Refrigerate.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and roll into small balls.
Place in refrigerator until cool.
Then melt chocolate and paraffin and dip balls in chocolate leaving top half undipped.

title: micro cauliflower au gratin dijon
directions: In microwave, saute onion 3 minutes, covered, on High or saute in butter on stove.
Microwave whole cauliflower with 1/2 cup water for 7 to 9 minutes in a covered container.
Add mayonnaise and Dijon to sauteed onion and mix.
Pour mixture over cauliflower and add strips of the Swiss cheese sufficient to cover the top and sides of cauliflower.
Microwave, uncovered, approximately 2 minutes to melt cheese.
Enjoy.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown
sausage,
pepper and onion.
Put soup, water and salt in	a
pot	and
let
come to a boil.
Add rice and again bring to	a
boil
and cover.
Simmer for seven minutes.	Add sausage, onion
and pepper mixture.	Put in covered casserole and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: german bread dumplings
directions: Whisk together egg and milk.
Toss in bread cubes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Gradually stir in just enough flour to make mixture stick together.
Form into 2 balls.
Gently drop into boiling water and simmer until dumpling comes to the top of the water.
Remove with a slotted spoon.
Drain and serve hot.
Makes 2 medium dumplings.

title: chicken papaya
directions: Saute garlic and ginger in vegetable oil until golden brown. Add chicken.
Let simmer until water is dry.
Add patis; let it simmer again until water is completely gone and when the oil starts to sizzle.
Then add 5 cups of water.
Let it boil and then simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add the papaya.
Cook the papayas until tender.
Then serve.

title: rice and beans stuffed peppers(microwave)
directions: In a one-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine corn, onion and water.
Cook, covered, on 100% power for 2 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce, uncooked rice, sugar and pepper.
Cook, covered, on High 2 to 3 minutes or until bubbly, stirring after 1 minute. Drain beans and stir into rice mixture.
Cover and set aside.

title: snickers salad
directions: Deseed the apples.
Cut up apples, bananas and Snickers bars. Mix well with Cool Whip and pudding mix.
Chill.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and celery in butter until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add flour and blend.
Add tomatoes gradually; stir constantly.
Add salt, pepper, sugar, bay leaf and parsley. Cook gently 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and parsley.
Add shrimp and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat.
Serve Shrimp Creole over rice.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix well together and add to cleaned pepper shells.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Add 1/4 cup water and pour catsup over the peppers and bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudge topped brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine margarine, sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, eggs, milk and 1 1/2 teaspoons vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 40 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Just before brownies are done, in heavy saucepan, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and remaining vanilla.
Immediately spread over hot brownies.
Cool.
Chill.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36 to 40 brownies.

title: no bake cookies (vanilla)
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter for 3 minutes (soft ball).
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Crumble soda crackers and add to liquid.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.

title: venison
directions: Place deer loin in a large baking dish.
Top with onion.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over the meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Good with rice.

title: delicious meat balls
directions: Mix and pour over
meatballs
and bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican style eggplant
directions: On 10 x 15-inch nonstick baking sheet, arrange eggplant slices in a single layer.
Bake at 450° until soft, about 20 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: can can chili
directions: Drain and rinse all beans, except for pork & beans.
In a 6-quart pan, heat the olive oil.
Add the chopped garlic and onion.
Cook for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Start adding cans of beans, stirring to mix; continue with all the dashes.
Lower heat, stir occasionally and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve by itself or over white rice.
You may also sprinkle sharp Cheddar cheese, and/or tortilla chips and broil for a few minutes until the cheese is melted.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Cream butter.
Stir in oats, sugar, syrup and vanilla.
Spread mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Don't bake any longer, even though bars do not look cooked.

title: party chicken salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1 cup chicken broth; heat and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Add remaining broth.
Beat in sour cream until smooth.
Add onion and salt.
Chill until partly set.
Add chicken, olives and celery.
Turn into a 3 1/2 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and vanilla in medium mixing bowl; set aside.
In double boiler melt chocolate chips and butter and add to sugar mixture.
Spread on buttered plate.
Cool in refrigerator for half hour or so.
Then eat!

title: pagache(slavic pizza)
directions: Peel, cube and boil potato in 1 cup water and a sprinkle of salt.
When tender, drain (saving liquid).
Add enough water to make the 1 cup of water called for in box directions.
Add ingredients called for on package.
After kneading the dough, let it rest 5 minutes.
Roll into a rectangle.
Add garlic powder to melted margarine and brush half of it on the dough.
Mash the potato and pat over the dough.
Sprinkle on the cheese.

title: all-purpose crepe batter 2
directions: Mixer or Whisk Method:
Combine eggs and salt.
Gradually add flour alternately with milk, beating with mixer or whisk.
Beat in butter or oil.

title: "lo-cal blueberry turnovers"
directions: Spray well with butter flavored nonstick spray sandwich maker (grill).
Put bread on grill.
Top with berries and sprinkle with artificial sweetener.
Spray the other side of bread and cover the berries.
Close sandwich maker and cook until done, about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: In a small saucepan, combine chopped white chocolate, milk, the 1 Tbsp. butter, and the vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium low heat until chocolate is melted.
Set aside to cool.
Meanwhile, for crust, in a small bowl, combine crushed graham crackers and the melted butter.
Press the crumb mixture onto the bottom and about 1 1/2 inches up the side of an 8 inch spring form pan.
Set pan aside.

title: dorothy emmons' slaw dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add vinegar, Miracle Whip and onion.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Makes approximately 2 quarts.
(I usually half this recipe for my own personal use.)

title: strawberry fruit salad
directions: Line platter with salad greens.
Arrange fruits in sections on platter.
Serve with lime sauce.

title: chalupa
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and tortillas.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread a layer of chicken mixture, then a layer of tortillas and cheese.
Repeat layering.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with warmed salsa and rice.
Serves 8.

title: baked french toast
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Diagonally cut bread into 1-inch slices and place in baking dish.
Set aside.

title: favorite dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except cream cheese in crock-pot or saucepan.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.
Add cream cheese and stir until melted.
Serve hot with Doritos.

title: curry pork dish with apples
directions: Cut up the meat in cubes and saute with curry in butter or margarine.
Saute for about 5 minutes while stirring.
Add onions and flour. Stir.
Add the salt, pepper and bouillon.
Simmer for about 10 minutes on low heat. Cut up the apples and tomatoes and add to the meat mixture. Cook for 15 minutes longer.
Correct seasonings, adding more spices to taste.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve over rice.

title: hawaiian beans and franks
directions: Slice hot dogs in 1-inch slices. Combine ingredients in a 2-quart casserole and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, then add peaches.
Combine milk, flour and sugar; mix and pour over oleo and peaches. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: easy hamburger macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger with salt, pepper, garlic, diced onion and green pepper.
Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain and rinse macaroni in cool water.
Put macaroni in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Drain hamburger and add Ragu; mix well, then add to macaroni.
Stir in cheese and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mardi gras punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, stir together concentrates and apple juice.
Stir in ginger ale.
Scoop sherbet into balls and spoon into punch bowl.
Float ice cubes in bowl.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Cream the shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla until light
and fluffy. Stir flour into creamed mixture. Blend well.
Add chocolate and nuts. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: chinese noodle hot dish
directions: Brown meat.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until tender. Alternate in layers with Chinese noodles.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters with scissors.
Combine white sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Then take the biscuit quarters and coat them with the cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Next, take 1/2 cup brown sugar with 1/2 stick butter or margarine and boil for 1 minute.
Place the coated quarters in a well-greased loaf pan. Then pour brown sugar sauce over biscuits, making sure it is even. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Slice and enjoy.

title: beef steak - filipino style
directions: Marinate steak in soy sauce, salt, pepper and lemon.
Pan-fry in about 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil.
When steaks are cooked, remove from pan and put in a serving dish.
Add 2 teaspoons oil to remaining oil in the pan and pan-fry the onions until tender. Pile on top of the steaks and serve hot.

title: cherry waldorf salad
directions: Bring 3/4 cup of the apple juice to a boil in medium saucepan. Completely dissolve jello in boiling apple juice.
Combine the remaining 1/2 cup apple juice and ice cubes to measure 1 1/4 cups. Add to jello; stir until slightly thickened.
Remove unmelted ice.
Stir in fruit and celery.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in a little cooking oil.
Add ground beef and stir until brown.
Mix together all remaining ingredients except Doritos and cheese
and add to the hamburger meat.
Bring to a boil.
Butter a casserole dish and put a layer of crushed Doritos and layer of hamburger meat and continue layering.
Top with grated cheese.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: In large bowl combine condensed milk and lemon juice.
Stir in cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Freeze until firm.
Remove 10 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: tomato florentine(tortellini soup)
directions: Melt butter in heavy large saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute for 2 minutes.
Stir in broth and tortellini; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Mix in Parmesan; season with salt and pepper.
Simmer until tortellini are just tender.
Stir in tomatoes, spinach and basil.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: savory turkey burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and shape into 6 patties. Broil or barbecue 3-inches from heat source, 4 minutes on each side.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, cottage cheese, cucumber, onion and salt in a mixing bowl.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let cool.
Do not let get cold.
Add mandarin oranges and orange sherbet.
Mix, put in mold and refrigerate until set.

title: angel pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add to boiling water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add hot mixture to stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat until thick and fluffy; add vanilla.
Drain pineapple and pour into baked pie shell.
Cool.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together oil and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add apples and nuts.
The apples make moisture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Shape into balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Fritos.
Fritos are spread over salad.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Line pan with Twinkies, filling side up.
Mix pudding mix with milk.
Add Eagle Brand and Cool Whip.
Pour over Twinkies. Top with strawberries.

title: no-bake lemon pie
directions: Make Crust:
Combine crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Press into buttered 8-inch pie plate. Chill until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: lemon supreme pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar together.
Next add 1/4 cup Egg Beaters at a time (or 1 egg at a time).
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Beat cottage cheese with mixer until smooth or unlumpy.
Add other ingredients.
Mix.
Best if made several hours before serving.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
In medium bowl, stir thawed strawberries, eggs and oil.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, salt and nuts. Add berry mixture to dry ingredients and stir just until blended. Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick in center comes out clean.

title: homemade tortilla chips
directions: Cut stack of tortillas into 8 wedges each.
Spread wedges in a single layer on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with cumin and lite salt. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes, turning after about 5 minutes. Make sure you watch them closely to keep from over-browning. Store in an airtight container.
When serving, freshen the chips in the microwave about 45 seconds to 1 minute.
Let set about 5 to 10 minutes before eating so they can harden and cool.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and soda, cinnamon and salt. Combine salad oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Then add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add carrots, pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: lincoln log
directions: Sift together 1/2 cup sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating constantly.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add vanilla and fold in dry ingredients.
Then fold in egg whites.
Spread evenly in a greased and floured pan (15 1/2 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for about 25 minutes.
Roll up in towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
When cool, unroll and spread with filling (whipped cream or ice cream).
Roll and spread with chocolate icing or dust with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed shrimpgroves, texas
directions: Mix everything except crackermeal.
Take a peeled shrimp and pack mixture firmly around shrimp.

title: macaroni with tahini sauce
directions: Cook macaroni or spaghetti in salted boiling water.
Mash garlic and salt in large bowl.
Add tahini, mixing well.
Gradually add water, blending thoroughly, then add lemon juice.
Add parsley and macaroni to tahini sauce and toss thoroughly.
May be eaten hot or cold.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix cake
mix with the pudding mix. Add oil and 7-Up. Beat 2 minutes; add eggs and beat 2 minutes. Bake in 3 pans at 350°.

title: chiffon cheese delight
directions: Dissolve
jello
in boiling water and set aside.
Cream lemon juice,
sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Add jello mix
and this
mixture together.
Blend crumbs and oleo until mixture
is moist.
Spread
half
of
crumbs on bottom of 9 x 13-inch
pan and
add
first mixture, then sprinkle remaining crumbs on top and chill.
Makes 12 servings.

title: melon and prosciutto(alfresco summer dinner with leslie and bob e.)
directions: Discard rind from melons and thinly slice melon.
In a large bowl, drizzle melon with lemon juice and oil and lightly toss.
On each of four plates, decoratively arrange melon and Prosciutto. Serves 4.

title: one pot chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in a Dutch oven until tender. If you are using fresh mushrooms, saute at the same time. Arrange chicken in a layer over vegetables.
Add spaghetti in a layer.
Combine soup, broth, lemon juice, pepper and nutmeg and pour over spaghetti, making sure all spaghetti is moistened.
If using canned mushrooms, add to top.
Cover; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 to 20 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Garnish with grated Parmesan cheese or paprika if desired.

title: helen's sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and stir to cream.
Add rest of ingredients, except sweet potatoes.
Boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir as it thickens and smooths.
Drain sweet potatoes and lay in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour sauce over potatoes.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Decorate with mandarin oranges and marshmallows.
Bake again for 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal, butter and boiling water together; cover and let cool while mixing the remaining ingredients.
Beat eggs; add sugars and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add part of flour and part of oatmeal mixture to egg mixture alternately. Pour in 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry pecan pie
directions: Mix cherries, pecans and milk.
Then add whip cream (stiff). Mix with cherries.
Add lemon juice.
Mix well.
Put in baked pie crust and chill.

title: kidney beans and sausage
directions: Combine beans and water in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand for 1 hour. Return beans to heat and simmer for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove 1/2 cup of beans, mash and set aside.
Place oil in frying pan and cook onion, green pepper and garlic until limp. Add onion mixture to beans in saucepan along with tomato sauce, seasonings and sausage.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend in mashed beans and cook until thickened. Remove bay leaf.
Serve over parsleyed rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: monkey bread dessert
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar; put in a bowl.
Cut each biscuit into quarters and dip into sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Put a few pecans in bottom of a Bundt pan in a design that will be on top. Layer biscuits in pan, putting a few nuts between each layer. Melt butter, brown sugar and water over low heat.
Bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from pan while hot.
Let cool for 5 minutes and serve.

title: lace cookies
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on greased and floured cookie sheets. Spread evenly and thinly with a spatula.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes or until edges are brown.
Let stand 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet with large spatula.
Cookies will be very thin and lacy.
Cool thoroughly.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Blend cream cheese, pudding, sugar and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer pudding mixture, then cookies (crushed), then pudding mixture, ending with cookies.
Layer in a plastic plant pot. Cover with gummy worms or plastic flowers.

title: hash browns
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Put into large casserole dish and bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops, apples & stuffin'
directions: Place pork chops in bottom of baking dish. Put apple pie filling on top of pork chops. Mix stuff according to package. Cover apples with stuffing mix.

title: creamed english peas
directions: Heat peas in small pan.
In small skillet, mix butter and flour.
Cook over low heat for 1 minute.
Add sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir milk in quickly.
Continue cooking and stirring until mixture thickens.
Add to peas and mix gently.

title: ann's authentic spaghetti sauce
directions: Pour olive oil in a large pan or Dutch oven to cover bottom. Add garlic and onion.
When lightly browned and limp, add tomato paste, sauce and tomatoes.
Fill each can with water and add to pot.
Add sugar and salt.
Let simmer on very low heat.
Stir frequently.
Brown beef and pork in olive oil; sprinkle with salt. Add to sauce while simmering.

title: pepperoni chicken
directions: In large frying pan, cook chicken in olive oil until it turns white.
Remove chicken, add more olive oil and fry onions until clear.
Add pepperoni and chicken.
Cook five minutes, then add mushrooms, tomatoes, spaghetti sauce mix and wine.
Cook five minutes.
Add zucchini, cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes longer. Serve over rice.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix cornbread as directed and pour into 2 round cake pans. Bake and cool.
Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Spread 1/2 mixture over 1 layer of cornbread.
Place 1/2 bacon on top.
Stack other pan of cornbread on top.
Top with remaining mixture.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: bacon and tomato dip
directions: In small mixing bowl combine first 3 ingredients.
Beat until smooth; stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover
and chill several hours.

title: quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; cut into small bits.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon grease.
Chop onions, mushrooms and green pepper; saute in bacon grease.
Grate cheeses.

title: disappearing onions
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise until spreadable.
Take one slice of lunch meat and place green onion on far edge.
Spread cream cheese along length of onion and roll up to edge of meat slice.
Arrange on tray alone or along with other vegies on relish tray.
Great for cookouts.
Watch them disappear.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish.
In a bowl add rest of ingredients, except fruit.
Pour into pan.
Pour peaches and juice on top.
Bake at 400° until crust forms and is golden brown.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and add milk and chicken broth. Cook 1 minute until thickened.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Let cool. Add ground chicken and salt to taste.
Chill.
With wet hands, roll in fine cracker crumbs (scant 1/4 cup), then in beaten egg with water, then in crumbs again.
Deep fry until golden.
Drain on paper towel.
Makes 8.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs and peel.
Boil vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper. Pour cooled brine in jars.
Add eggs.
Cover; let set 10 days.

title: beaufort bog
directions: While large pot of water is coming to a boil, break ears of corn in half and cut kielbasa into bite size pieces.
After water comes to a boil, add crab boil and corn.
Let cook for 15 minutes. Next, add kielbasa and let cook for 10 minutes.
Next, add shrimp and cook 1 to 2 minutes or until pink.
Drain and serve on a large platter.
Serve with cocktail sauce and a honey mustard for the kielbasa.
Great tasting and easy recipe for a crowd.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch and salt in a medium saucepan.
Add water, stirring until well blended.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Beat egg yolks and gradually add to mixture and cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, lemon rind and juice; stir until butter melts. Pour filling into pastry shell.
Beat egg whites and add sugar and cream of tartar.
Pour over pie.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except ham.
Spread thin layer of mixture evenly over one slice of ham.
With cheese side up, roll up ham slice.
Wrap in wax paper or Saran Wrap.
Chill for several hours or overnight.
With a sharp knife, slice into thin slices.
To hold together and make them easier to serve, put toothpick through each one.
Makes about 80.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles as you would for spaghetti, then drain in colander.
Mix with melted butter, orange juice, salt, sugar and cinnamon in large bowl.
Let mixture stand 1 hour.
Mix grated apple, raisins and eggs together; blend well with noodle mixture. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dot generously with butter; sprinkle cinnamon and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
I have not had to alter this recipe for elevation.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually stir in milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add onion and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Beat egg yolks; stir a small amount of hot sauce mixture into egg yolks.
Mix well.
Stir egg yolk mixture and spinach into sauce mixture.
Beat egg white until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into sauce mixture.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place casserole in a shallow baking pan. Fill pan 1-inch deep with water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Yield:
8 servings.

title: hamburger-rice casserole
directions: Layer rice, then corn, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Layer 1 can tomato sauce, 1/2 c. water, onions, green pepper and ground beef (uncooked).
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Layer 1 can tomato sauce, then 1/4 cup water.
Cover with bacon strips.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bacon is crisp.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Cool and drain.
Combine everything except crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole dish and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: marinated pork roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put roast and marinade in a tightly sealed bag overnight in refrigerator.
Turn and press occasionally to distribute marinade.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream margarine, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Shape in 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Crisscross with fork tines.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pan.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mock steak
directions: Mix ingredients and pack into large baking dish.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.
Cut in squares, flour and brown in oil. Place meat back in baking dish.
Add 1 can mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk to meat drippings.
Pour over meat and bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, chill overnight.
This is good for cookouts.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, salt, butter and boiling water until clear and thick.
Put sweet potatoes, apples and sauce in layers in casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.
(I prefer 60 minutes.)

title: slaw
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric for 3 minutes.
Pour over chopped cabbage, onions and bell peppers while it is still hot.

title: quick cranberry-orange jello salad
directions: Add 2 1/2 cups boiling water to jello; stir until dissolved. Add 12 to 15 ice cubes and stir.
Set in refrigerator until slightly solid (usually 30 minutes or so).
Add cranberries, nuts and drained orange segments.
Pour into mold that has been sprayed with Pam.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover with a top crust, crimp edges.
Slit top crust and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: honey bran bread
directions: Empty bran in a large bowl.
Add buttermilk, honey, eggs, oil, flour, oatmeal and soda.
Mix well.
Add raisins last.
Bake at 375° until tester comes out clean.
Makes two large loaves or 3 small ones.

title: california chili
directions: Into heavy, deep pot, add meat with a little bacon drippings. Cook until meat is brown.
Add onion, bell pepper, garlic, crushed red pepper, tomato sauce, enchilada sauce and ginger ale.
Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add more ginger ale if liquid is needed.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Drain pineapple and reserve the juice. Put pineapple in the dish.
Mix sugar and flour; drizzle over the pineapple.
Sprinkle cheese over the top of that.
Drizzle 3 tablespoons of juice on top.
Mix margarine and cracker crumbs; spread over the top of casserole.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 30 minutes.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar, oatmeal and vanilla together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together. Chill about 2 hours before serving.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce oven heat to 325°
and bake for 30 minutes.

title: mississippi barbecue party rolls
directions: Rinse chicken. Marinate with Mississippi barbecue sauce and grill over open flame. While chicken is grilling, mix corn, tomatoes, onions and bell peppers. Set aside. Mix sour cream and yogurt. Pour half the mixture over the vegetables. Once chicken is grilled, cut chicken into strips and marinate with more barbecue sauce. Open crescent rolls and lay them out singly on an ungreased cookie sheet. Place a strip of chicken at the wide end of the dough and spoon a tablespoon of the corn mixture on top of chicken. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and roll up with end of dough. Do this with each crescent roll strip, placing each on the cookie sheet. Bake rolls at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until brown. Serve garnished with remaining corn mixture and sour cream/yogurt sauce. Salsa can be served as a dipping sauce also.

title: corn and tomatoes
directions: Cut corn off cob.
Put corn in frying pan.
Put enough water to cover corn good.
Bring to a boil and let cook on medium-low until water boils out of corn.
Then put butter in corn and cut up onion in corn; let fry until butter is out of bottom of pan.
When corn is done, then cut up tomato in it and stir.

title: crustless crab quiche
directions: Saut mushrooms and onions in butter; drain off excess liquid. In a blender or food processor, blend eggs, sour cream, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, flour, salt and hot pepper sauce. Pour into a large bow. Stir in mushrooms and onions, Monterey Jack cheese and crab meat. Pour into a lightly buttered 10-inch pie plate or shallow casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Sprinkle apple slices with cinnamon sugar, if desired, and roll each slice in
a crescent roll triangle, starting at large end.
Place in baking dish.
In a saucepan bring sugar, water and margarine to a boil.
Pour over crescent rolls.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: bisque tortoni
directions: In small bowl, beat yolks with sugar until fluffy.
Stir in liquid (vanilla and brandy).
Fold egg yolks into egg whites and the egg white mixture into the whipped cream.
Stir in crushed macaroons.
Fill 8 cupcake papers or pretty dessert glasses. Serve with chocolate laced cookies.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use cupcake papers in muffin pans. Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon in mixing bowl.
Mix applesauce, oil and eggs together.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Do not overmix.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 to 3/4 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.

title: salmon spread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 8 ingredients; mix well. Spread on a serving platter and shape into a loaf or ball.
Top with sour cream.
Garnish with dill or parsley if desired.
Serve with bread rounds or crackers.
Yields 8 to 10 appetizer servings.

title: chili corn bread casserole
directions: Cook beef in large, heavy kettle or Dutch oven, stirring until meat loses its red color.
Add onion and garlic and cook about 2 minutes longer.
Add 1/2 cup water and remaining ingredients, except beans and topping.
Bring to boil and simmer, stirring often, 10 minutes.
Add beans and simmer about 5 minutes longer. Put in 3-quart casserole and cover with topping.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: layered party cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve 1 package raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Add 1/4 cup cold water and 1/4 cup wine and chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in cranberry sauce, apple and walnuts.
Pour into 2 quart serving dish.
Chill until set, but not firm.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened, then blend in mayonnaise and whipped topping.
Pour over gelatin in dish.
Chill until set, but not firm.
Dissolve remaining raspberry gelatin in remaining boiling water.
Add remaining cold water and wine.
Chill until slightly thickened. Pour into dish over lemon layer.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with sugared green grapes, if desired.
Makes 12 servings, 6 3/4 cups.

title: caviar artichoke delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and artichoke hearts with mixer.
Add grated onion.
Mold into a circle on a serving tray.
Before serving, spread caviar on top of cream cheese mixture and place grated egg on top of caviar.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot spiced percolator punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, cranberry juice and brown sugar. Place in 30-cup automatic coffeemaker and add water.
Combine spices and put in basket or coffeemaker.
Perk and serve hot. Makes 20 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper in butter.
Mix all together.
Pour in baking dish.
Top with almonds, if desired. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water until they are fork-tender. Do not overcook. Drain and cool. While cooling, make a marinade with rest of ingredients and pour over carrots. Refrigerate before serving. Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 10 1/2-inch skillet or 2-quart baking dish.
Set aside.
Brown sausage and onion in medium skillet.
Drain well.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine ingredients, and let set overnight.
Next day, rinse in cold water; drain.
Then rinse again; drain well.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg, molasses and sour milk.
Sift together the flour, salt, cinnamon, ginger and baking soda; add to molasses mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Roll on a well floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter; sprinkle with sugar. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin bread pudding
directions: In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine cookies and apple; set aside.
In small bowl, blend milk, egg product, brown sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cookie mixture; let stand for 5 minutes. Cover; bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover; bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until set.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm or cold with whipped topping, if desired.

title: egg sandwich
directions: Cook the eggs.
Scramble the eggs.
Get the mayonnaise out. Toast the bread.
Put mayonnaise on the bread.
Put eggs on the bread.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together the flour, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Add eggs and undrained fruit cocktail; mix by hand until well-blended.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes clean.
While cake is baking, prepare icing.

title: diabetic chunky peanut butter cookies(this is a diabetic recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In small bowl, mix flour and baking powder. In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine, peanut butter, sugar and Sweet 'N Low until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla. Stir in flour mixture and peanuts. On waxed paper, shape dough into a roll about 1 x 9 x 1/2-inch. Dough will be slightly sticky. Wrap in waxed paper; refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush graham crackers and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter and pour over crackers.
Mix together and make a crust.

title: ham ball
directions: Break ham into chunks with a fork, add cream cheese, onion and liquid smoke.
Form into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Crush cookies until VERY fine. Add dates, raisins and nuts. Stir in milk. mix well. It will be very sticky and a bit yucky looking, but don't let this bother you. Line a loaf pan with wax paper. Put mixture in pan, cover with wax paper and press. The harder you pack it down, the better it will taste. Leave in pan and covered with wax paper. Put in the refrigerator overnight. The next day it can be removed from the pan but needs to stay covered. It is very firm, very rich, and tastes MUCH better than it looks. Candied fruit can be added if desired. Golden raisins can be added in place of dates.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together, put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with cheese. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Halve a 1 1/2-pound squash lengthwise.
If squash is hard to cut, microwave for 1 to 2 minutes.
Scrape out the seeds.
Fit the halves together again or cover each with plastic wrap.
Microwave for 1/2 time.
Turn over the whole squash or rotate and rearrange halves.
Microwave remaining time.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes. High power:
1/2 squash 5 to 8 minutes; 1 squash 8 1/2 to 11 1/2 minutes; 2 squash 13 to 16 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecan mix.
Pour in shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: taco snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine cereal, pretzels, tortilla chips and taco seasoning mix. Drizzle with margarine, tossing to coat well. Store in airtight container.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Scald half the milk and add 1/2 cup of the sugar and the salt. Bring to a boil. Mix flour, cornstarch and beaten egg and yolks with the remaining milk and beat until smooth. Add a little of the hot milk and blend. Combine both mixtures and cook over hot water, stirring frequently. Remove and add

the butter and flavorings. Beat until smooth. Beat egg whites until frothy; add remaining sugar and beat until stiff. Fold the custard into the egg whites. Sprinkle 1/4 cup coconut through the mixture and pour into a baked shell. Whip the cream and spread over the top. Cover with rest of the coconut and chill.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix top 6 ingredients and put into pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Take one 9 x 13-inch cake pan, layer bottom of cake pan with crackers.
Then layer cabbage on top of crackers.
Then put thin slices of butter on cabbage.
Then put layers of cheese over butter, then fill pan with milk until you can see it.
Bake at 350° until milk dries out of it.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: 30 minutes apple butter
directions: Bring to a boil.
Boil 20 minutes.
Add cinnamon heart candy. Boil 10 minutes longer.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover; cook for 25 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Serves 6.

title: casserole bread-herb parmesan
directions: Combine 1/2 cup cheese, 3 cups flour and other ingredients. Beat 2 minutes; add rest of flour.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Beat down; turn into pan.
Sprinkle with one teaspoon cheese.
Bake 55 minutes at 375°.
Especially good sliced and made into Melba toast.

title: west coast lefse(vest kyst lefse)
directions: Mix as for bread.
Dough should be a little firmer than bread. Let rise.
Knead down and let rise again until light.
Divide into good sized biscuits and cover with damp cloth to keep from drying out.
Roll each piece out on floured cloth with grooved rolling pin until thin.
This is difficult, as dough springs back. Use sharp, pointed rolling pin to mark.
Bake on hot, greased griddle, turning as one side browns.
Spread out cakes until cool and crisp.
Makes about 50.

title: delicious deli salad
directions: Cook rotini; drain.
Add all other ingredients and toss well. Cover.
Chill thoroughly.
Toss before serving.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine
first 4 ingredients in a saucepan and boil for 1
1/2 minutes.
After
removing	from
burner
add all other ingredients.
Mix and drop on wax paper.

title: traditional minestrone
directions: Heat oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. Add onions, carrots, garlic and celery. Cook, stirring occasionally, until carrots are slightly soft, about 10 minutes. Add green beans, broth and tomatoes to pot. Bring soup to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Add macaroni, beans and basil. Simmer, covered, until macaroni is tender, about 10 minutes. Ladle soup into bowls. Top each with Parmesan cheese.

title: linguine and cheese
directions: Cook and drain noodles. Rinse with hot water and drain again. Mix sauce ingredients. Cook and stir over low heat until cheeses melt and sauce is well blended.
Pour over noodles, coating well. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons Parmesan on top.

title: barbecue cheese fries
directions: Cook French fries.
Heat barbecue sauce.
Melt the cheese in a container.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: western casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Drain.
Stir in corn, kidney beans, tomato soup, cheese, milk, onion and chili powder.
Bring to boil. Turn into casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Mix 1 or more boxes corn muffin mix to cover top of casserole.
Bake 20 minutes longer or until corn bread is golden brown and done.

title: tri-colore linguine with sun-dried tomatoes and peas(yield: 4 servings)
directions: Cook peas until tender, yet firm; drain and set aside.
Cook the pasta in boiling salted water, following the directions on the packet carefully to avoid overcooking.

title: lemon cake
directions: Make and bake cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make small holes in cooled cake with a wooden spoon handle every 2-inches.

title: marinated shrimp in fresh dill(to serve before dinner with wassail)
directions: Bring salted water, dill seed and sliced lemon to boil.
Add shrimp and simmer until the shrimp are pink, about 3 to 4 minutes. Immediately drain and chill the shrimp.
Peel and devein shrimp. Place them in a crock or bowl.

title: mrs. elizabeth jackson's graham cracker candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until soft ball stage then add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add cracker crumbs and nuts. Stir until well mixed.
Drop on wax paper or pour into a buttered dish.
When cool, cut into serving pieces.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Add sugar, flour and soda to well beaten eggs. Add vanilla and pineapple with juice. Beat by hand. Bake in ungreased 10 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until top turns a golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, vanilla, salt and cinnamon. Beat mixture well. Add oil, soda, baking powder and flour. Beat this mixture well. Add zucchini and chopped nuts. Pour into two 2-pound loaf pans or four 1-pound loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Heat 1 cup sour cream to lukewarm in saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in 3 tablespoons sugar, 1/2 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon salt.
Crumble cake yeast (or package dry yeast).
Stir until dissolved.
Add egg, 2 tablespoons soft shortening and flour. Mix well, using hand if necessary.
Turn onto a floured board. Fold over until smooth.
Roll into a 24 x 6-inch oblong.
Spread 2 tablespoons soft butter.
Sprinkle half the dough with a mixture of 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Fold other half over. Cut into 24 strips 1-inch wide.
Fold strip at both ends and twist opposite direction.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Cover and let rise about 1 hour.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Frost.

title: broccoli with stuffing casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Cook herb stuffing mix as directed.
Combine egg, onion, soup and mayonnaise.
Place layer of broccoli in a 2-quart casserole.
Add layer of cheese.
Pour small amount of sauce on top.
Repeat layers until all are used. Top with cooked stuffing mix.
Pour butter on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix all the ingredients just until moist.
Makes 1 loaf or 12 muffins. Cook at 325° for 18 to 20 minutes for muffins or 35 to 40 minutes for bread.

title: busy day cake
directions: Place shortening in mixing bowl.
Sift in dry ingredients. Add egg and half the milk; mix until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add remaining milk and vanilla; beat 2 minutes longer.
Bake in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch lightly floured baking pan at 375° for about 25 minutes, or until done.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together the first five ingredients.
In a small bowl; combine egg, milk, oil and vanilla. Add the liquid mixture to the dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
The batter should be lumpy.
Grease muffin cups or line them with paper cups.
Fold the raspberries into the batter and pour into cups.
Sprinkle tops with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti; add Parmesan cheese, eggs, seasoning and herbs.
Press together into 3 greased 9-inch pie pans.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Grease foil and cover pans.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 5 more minutes.
Cut pies into 8 slices.
Top with favorite tomato sauce.
Serves 8 to 10 people.
Makes 3 pies.

title: tabasco omelette loaf
directions: In a bowl, mix breadcrumbs, pepper, tomato, chives and Tabasco.
Season with salt and a little pepper.
Beat the egg yolks and blend into the mixture.
Whisk the whites until stiff and fold in.

title: chocolate frosting recipe\(no-cooking)
directions: Blend all together thoroughly.
Makes enough for 4 medium size layers.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar in large plastic bag. Cut biscuits into fourths and shake in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Drop coated biscuits into lightly greased Bundt pan. Melt
margarine, brown sugar and nuts; bring to a boil. Pour mixture over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat out on jelly roll pan the pizza or roll dough.
Bake for 6 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: cherry delight
directions: Put cherry pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry white cake mix on top.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Pour melted butter over all.
(Try to pour evenly over all of cake mix.)
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until topping is brown.

title: soft chocolate chippers
directions: Add a teaspoon of vinegar or lemon juice to milk if no buttermilk.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook for 10 to 15 minutes on 350° and then top with Topping.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into shortening mixture.
Let stand a few minutes.
Roll dough out onto a floured surface to desired thickness.
Yield:
4 (9-inch) pie shells or pastry for 2 double crust pies.

title: virginia applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening; add egg and sauce.
Sift flour before measuring.
(Sift some over nuts.)
Dissolve soda in hot water. Add alternately with flour to mixture.
Add raisins and nuts. Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour at 350°, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Time may vary.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into thirds.
Cook and drain.
Place everything remaining into blender; whirl until pepper and carrot are coarsely chopped.
Pour over cooked spaghetti.
Let set overnight; stir occasionally.
If spaghetti is slightly warm it will absorb more flavor.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Combine brown sugar, 4 cups hot water and 2 tablespoons butter in 9 x 13-inch pan; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Cream sugar and remaining butter.
Add dry ingredients with sour milk.
Fold in raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Blend in blender and pour in 4 sherbet cups.
Freeze 1 hour only.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and beat 20 minutes with hand mixer or 5 to 7 minutes in food processor.
Add vinegar and celery seed; beat again until well mixed.
Put in a jar and store in refrigerator.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet (you choose the size).
Bake 20 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheets.

title: pineapple chiffon pie
directions: Mix sugar, pineapple and eggs.
Boil about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 package lime Jell-O. Let stand until cold.
Whip chilled milk; fold in cooked mixture. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit salad deluxe(quick and delicious!)
directions: In large bowl, combine all fruit.
With electric mixer, blend sour cream, sugar and vanilla until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over fruit and stir.
Stir in instant pudding mix and blend.
Fold in marshmallows; chill and serve.
Recipe makes 8 servings.
Fat-free.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Separate whites of 4 of 5 eggs for meringue.
Add yolks and whole egg to mixture.
Add milk and vanilla.
Melt butter and mix well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour mixture into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake approximately 30 minutes until only shakes little in middle.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add 5 tablespoons sugar.
Beat until sugar is melted.
Put on top of pies and brown in oven.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells as directed. Cool. Brown hamburger. Drain and mix with onions, egg, cottage cheese, Mozzarella and Cheddar cheeses. Stuff shells with hamburger and cheese mixture. Place small amount of sauce in a 9 x 13 pan. Place stuffed shells on top. Pour remaining sauce over shells. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake in a 450° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rice and green chili pilaf
directions: In a small heavy saucepan, saute onion in oil over moderately low heat.
Stir in garlic, chilies and rice, stirring occasionally, until rice is translucent, about 1 minute.
Add broth, salt and pepper to taste and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook, covered, until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, about 20 minutes.
Use a fork to fluff pilaf and add scallion.

title: stir-fried rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet (Teflon works best) saute onion, carrot and bell pepper until tender.
Add rice and heat thoroughly.
Stir in eggs and meat and fry on medium-high heat for a few minutes.
Add soy sauce and black pepper to taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli slightly and drain.
Add soup, mayonnaise, egg, cheese and onion.
Mix and pour into casserole dish.
Melt butter in pan and pour in stuffing mix.
Stir.
Pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sin pie
directions: Melt butter and mix with flour and pecans. Put into a 9 x 12 glass pan, covering the entire bottom of the pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and let cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies with oatmeal
directions: Sift flour once before measuring, then sift with soda and salt.
Cream shortening until soft.
Add sugar gradually, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add hot water to creamed mixture, then sifted dry ingredients.
Add nuts, chips, oatmeal and vanilla; mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven about 8 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: date cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add sugar, butter and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and vanilla and add to mixture.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Bring to a boil in the same water. Pour off and add fresh water, salt and pinch of baking soda.
Boil gently for 1 hour.
Drain if there is too much water left.

title: doris's quiche
directions: Mix Bisquick, cheese, garlic, parsley and scallion.
Add oil and beaten eggs.
Add vegetables of choice.
Put in greased pie plate. Add pinches on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry orange mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Put cranberries and orange, including rind, through food chopper with coarse blade.
Stir in sugar. Let stand at room temperature about 5 minutes.
Stir in thickened gelatin.
Pour into a 1-quart mold and chill until firm.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in oil until done.
Take out of skillet.
Add to oil in skillet the onion soup mix and the 2 cans soup.
Let simmer until mixed good, then add cooked pork chops.
Let simmer together for 5 or 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in a greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake slowly and brown top, 45 to 50 minutes.

title: double crispy chicken
directions: Place cereal in a shallow pan and set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, beat together egg and milk.
Add flour, salt and pepper, mix until smooth.
Dip chicken in batter, then coat with cereal.
Place in a single layer, skin side up, in foil lined shallow pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.

title: cocoa fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter or margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Add cocoa; heat just until mixture begins to boil, stirring constantly.
Pour into a small mixer bowl.
