Alternately add confectioners sugar and milk, beating to spreading consistency. Blend in vanilla.
Spread frosting while warm.
Fills and frosts an 8 or 9-inch layer cake.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Mix and beat until well blended.
Cook in diced fried bacon until thick. Cool.
If used for potato salad, add 1 teaspoon mustard and 1/2 pint light cream.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread 1/2 cookie dough onto a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Spread over cooled cookie dough.
Spread pie filling on cream cheese mixture.
Arrange fruit over pie filling.
Put Cool Whip on top of fruit.
Arrange cherries and nuts on top of Cool Whip.

title: duncan's sensational chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and eggs together.
Separately sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in chips, oatmeal and vanilla.
Blend well.
Drop by tablespoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until light golden brown at 375°.
Enjoy!

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Place ribs in slow cooker.
In bowl, combine tomato soup, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce, celery seed and chili powder.
Pour over ribs.
Cook until tender.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Boil the water and add the oatmeal.
Let this stand for 20 minutes.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pot pie
directions: Cook meat, being sure to have lots of liquid with it.
If it's a large piece, cut into bite-size portions.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Rinse shrimp; remove shells, leaving tails on.
Devein.
Wash under cold running water.
Drain and pat dry.
Melt butter or margarine in a shallow baking pan.
Add salad oil, 2 tablespoons parsley, garlic, salt, cayenne and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add shrimp, tossing or stirring lightly in butter mixture to coat well.
Arrange in a single layer in the pan.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes longer or until red and lightly browned.
Serve shrimp with remaining chopped parsley sprinkled over the mixture.
Serves 8.

title: a capella chicken enchilada
directions: In skillet, brown onion in butter.
Add soups, broth and chilies.
Add chicken and mix well.
In large baking dish, layer portions of tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers until dish is filled, ending with cheese.
Let stand for several hours before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: harvard beets #1
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Combine sugar and cornstarch. Stir in vinegar and beet liquid or water.
Stir over low heat until thickened.
Add beets and butter.
Heat.
Ready to be served.

title: italian green vegetable salad
directions: Mix well with canned ingredients.
Pour oil mixture over vegetables.
Let set overnight.

title: ice tea drink
directions: Splash of sour mix, fill glass with Coke.

title: caesar salad with pasta and vegetables
directions: Layer half each of pasta and vegies in a 2 1/2-quart bowl. Drizzle with salad dressing as you layer.
Cover and chill 8 hours. Toss before serving.
Serves 10.

title: quick strawberry cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip with one cup of confectioners sugar.
Cut angel food cake into 2 layers.
Top first layer with strawberry preserves.
Then cover with Cool Whip mix.
Add second layer of angel food cake.
Cover again with strawberry preserves.
Then cover entire cake with remainder of Cool Whip mix.
Place strawberries on top.

title: chili for 100
directions: Add water as needed.
Cook for 3 hours.

title: simple vanilla pudding
directions: In saucepan, heat 1 1/2 cups milk and sugar to simmer in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Mix 1/2 cup milk and cornstarch in cup. Stir into hot milk.
Stir constantly over medium heat until thickened and starting to boil, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir about 1/2 cup of hot mixture into beaten eggs.
Dribble egg mixture into pan and stir over low heat for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 4 servings.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine; add brown sugar and eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add margarine mixture to flour mixture until well blended.
Add chocolate chip morsels.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat and stir in brown sugar.
Cool. Beat in egg.
Sift dry ingredients; stir into brown sugar mixture. Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.

title: aunt nema's cream candy
directions: Boil to hard ball stage.
Do not stir after starts to boil. Do not scrape pan.
Pour on marble slab (this must be genuine marble).
Fold outside edges in as candy begins to cool.
As soon as candy is cool enough to handle, pull as you would taffy.
Cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: crab and cheese wontons
directions: Beat cream cheese, sesame oil, soy sauce and pepper until smooth.
Mix in chives and crab.
Fill wontons with 1 teaspoon of mixture.
In a wok, heat 1 to 1 1/2 inches of oil to 350°.
Fry 4 to 6 wontons at a time until golden.
If made ahead of time, wrap airtight and freeze.
To reheat, arrange on a baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with plum sauce for dipping.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: Soften banana with fork.
Mix banana, eggs, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Make a well in the middle of the dry ingredients and pour in banana mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon into greased muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: fruit slush
directions: Combine ingredients and freeze in 5 to 7 plastic cups.
Sit out 20 minutes before serving.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Remove core of cabbage; discard.
Bring to boil in rice cooker with 2 cups water.
Turn off until needed.
Mix other ingredients well.
Put 2 tablespoons of mixture in each cabbage loaf.
Fold and place in large pot with oil and water.
Cook until tender.
May also be cooked in rice cooker.

title: cream cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add water to make 3/4 cup. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Let the Jell-O partially set, then stir in pineapple, cream cheese and nuts.
Add the cherries, if desired.

title: corn flake crunch cookies
directions: Melt first
4 ingredients in double boiler, then add corn flakes.
Stir until well coated.
Drop tablespoon size balls on wax paper and cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs and milk. Stir in crackers, onion, parsley, salt, sage and 1/8 teaspoon pepper. Add beef; mix well. Pat into a 5 1/2-cup ring; unmold in shallow baking pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes or pat mixture into 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake for 1 1/4 hours. Spoon off fat.
Combine catsup, sugar and mustard. Spread over meat. Return for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Grease a 13 X 9 casserole dish.
Spoon mixture into casserole dish.
Bake at 350 for
45 minutes to an hour, uncovered.

title: quesadillas
directions: Combine cheese, bacon, tomato, onions and ham in a bowl.
Mix well.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over half the tortillas to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Top with remaining tortillas.
Spray skillet with Pam.
Cook quesadillas 1 to 2 minutes on each side until lightly browned and cheese melts.
Cut into four wedges each. Serve with shredded lettuce, sour cream, and/or guacamole.

title: lemon dill fish
directions: Stir salad dressing, juice, peel and dill until blended. Place fish on greased grill or rack or broiler pan.
Brush with half of sauce.
Grill or broil for 5 to 8 minutes; turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Continue grilling or broiling for 5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Makes 4 servings. Preparation time: 5 minutes.
Cooking time: 16 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water with skins on.
Do not overcook. Peel and cut up quickly while hot.
Marinate with the oil and vinegar in which the mashed garlic has been soaking.

title: cake icing
directions: Mix all ingredients, spread on cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: scallops with pasta and avocado
directions: Heat oil and butter in a large nonaluminum skillet over medium heat.
Add scallops and saute until barely firm, about 2 minutes. Using slotted spoon, transfer to mixing bowl.
Increase heat to medium-high.
Add shallots and onions and saute until soft.
Stir in garlic and herbs; cook 1 minute.
Add wine and cook 2 minutes. Stir in tomatoes.
Increase heat to high and boil briefly until sauce is thick.
Stir in cream and sugar and cook another 20 seconds.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add to scallops, mixing gently.
Toss with hot pasta and divide equally among serving plates.
Top with avocado.
Scallops can be prepared one day ahead.
Reheat gently before adding pasta.

title: mom's peanut kisses
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Shape into balls, about 1 teaspoon each, and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press Kisses in center so dough will form over edge.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: snowy mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water (salted) until tender.
Drain and return pan to low heat, shaking to dry potatoes.
In a large bowl of electric mixer, cream together cheese and sour cream.
Add potatoes, one at a time, to cream mixture; continue beating on high speed until light and fluffy.
On low speed, add minced scallions, celery, green pepper, parsley, 1/4 cup melted butter, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Spoon into 2 1/2 to 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers.

title: zesty meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook meatballs in hot oil until lightly browned.
Drain. Place meatballs in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cook over medium heat 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Pour sauce over meatballs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: waldorf crown salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts.
Pour into 5 cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and surround with lettuce.
Fill center with Regal Dressing.
Garnish with apple slices and walnut half, if desired.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make loaf.
Bake for about 1 hour or until done.
Check with toothpick.

title: rich peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, butter, peanut butter and sugars. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Stir in creamed mixture and mix well. Shape the soft dough into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: molded raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add raspberries and pineapple. Pour half of mixture in mold.
Freeze until firm.
Spread sour cream on first layer, then add rest of mixture on top of sour cream layer.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
Serves 12.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon and olives.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Ingredients may be mixed the day before and refrigerated until time to bake.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and cook carrots; drain.
Slice pepper and onion; mix with carrots in medium-size bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Pour over carrots and let stand overnight.

title: hankie pankie
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain.
Add cheese; stir until melted. Add remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture on single slices of bread.
Place on cookie sheet; freeze.
When frozen, store in freezer bags.
When ready to use, place on cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
May be microwaved, if desired.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt Milky Ways in double boiler.
Pour all ingredients in freezer and fill with milk.
Freeze.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: ancini fruit salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Mix and boil the sugar, fruit juices, salt and flour for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Add small amount of hot mixture to 2 beaten eggs.
Add eggs back to hot mixture and boil an additional 2 minutes.
Add lemon juice. Cool and pour over ancini and fruit.
Chill thoroughly.
Before serving add Cool Whip.

title: karo fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch square baking pan with spray.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients until well mixed. In medium bowl, whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs, then mix in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and pineapple.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rum cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil, water and rum.
Beat for 10 minutes.
Pour batter into greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
While cake is still hot, pour over rum glaze.

title: taco dip
directions: In double boiler or microwave, melt Velveeta cheese and Cheddar cheese.
After melted, add tomatoes.
Don't drain.
Add ground beef mixture to cheese mixture.
Stir and serve in chafing dish or fondue pot.
Serve warm with taco chips and/or vegetables.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients together and store in airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup for each cup of boiling water.

title: baked round steak
directions: Remove bone and fat from steak.
Place in 12-inch Dutch oven and
cover	with sliced onions.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over steak.
Bake 1 hour.

title: spoon bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add beaten egg, oil and sugar. Gradually add flour; mix well after each addition.
These are ideal baked in muffin tins, filling the tins about half full (spoon in tins).
Bake at 375° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Use what dough is needed, it will keep several days in the refrigerator in a covered bowl.

title: swiss-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems and set aside.
Sprinkle inside of caps with salt.
Chop stems finely; saute in butter over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except mushroom caps, mixing well.

title: cherry pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in bowl and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Tomatoes do well in a food processor.
In another small bowl, mix spices.
Pour over tomatoes; mix well before pouring into crust.
Top with second crust.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until brown on top.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately milk and the flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Lastly, add vanilla extract and almond extract and fold in contents of coconut.
Bake in greased and floured large tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300° or until cake tests done.
Cake makes its own topping.

title: pistolettes
directions: Cook ground meat with onion.
Cook broccoli.
After broccoli is cooked, mix with cut up Velveeta cheese, ground meat and onion. Scoop out rolls.
Save cut off end to put back on with toothpick after stuffing with meat mixture.
Freeze.
Do not cook before freezing.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Blend berries and honey until smooth.
Add the ice cream and 1 cup of milk and blend again.
Add remaining milk and blend 20 seconds.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Make into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 300.
Lightly grease a 9 X 13 baking dish.
In a large bowl, beat together butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into prepared baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 300.

title: hawaiian fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients and chill overnight for best results.

title: roast potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut into cubes.
In plastic bag, add remaining ingredients; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Turn every 15 minutes.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: (Use no substitutes.)
In bag combine flour, paprika and pepper.
Add chicken; shake to coat.
In skillet brown chicken in butter; remove.
In same skillet cook mushrooms.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 3 minutes.
Add chicken; simmer covered 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
You may have to add water occasionally as sauce cooks down quickly.
Serve with rice.

title: batter (spoon) bread
directions: Mix meal, salt and baking powder.
Add egg, beaten lightly, sweet milk and enough boiling water to make a very thin batter. Add butter and lard.
Put in well-greased baking dish; cook for 30 to 40 minutes in moderate oven (375°).
Serves 6.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, butter, salt and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in lemon juice and peel.
Add milk, beating slowly. Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold in.

title: cinnamon icebox cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon. Set aside.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Slice jalapeno peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove all seeds and internal structure.
Wash pepper halves and dry them.
Fill pepper halves with cream cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding and juice until thick, stirring constantly, as you would in making any pudding.
Cool and add fruit.

title: mother's banana nut bread
directions: Mix all
ingredients
in a large mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed
1/2 minute, then high speed for 3 minutes, scraping bowl often.
Pour
into
greased
and floured loaf pans and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mexican dip(microwave)
directions: Put into a microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High until cream cheese is melted and creamy.
Stir often.
Serve warm with taco chips.

title: oyster cracker nic nacs
directions: Mix dressing, dill and garlic with oil and pour over crackers. Mix well.
Let stand at least 1 hour.

title: la cours punch
directions: Combine lemon juice, pineapple chunks and sugar.
Immediately before serving, add remaining ingredients and pour over large chunks of ice.
This makes 11 gallons and is a lovely punch for receptions.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and fit into a well greased loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven for 1 hour. Cut in 1 inch slices and serve hot or cold.

title: cod and vegetable bake
directions: If fish fillets are large, cut into serving pieces.
Arrange fish in ungreased oblong baking dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inches or square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and the pepper.
Mix carrots, celery, onion, bread cubes, margarine, 1/2 teaspoon salt, sage and thyme.
Spread evenly over fish.
Mix bread crumbs, parsley and paprika; sprinkle over vegetables.
Cover and cook in 350° oven until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: grilled cheese pie
directions: Shred cheese.
Mix cheese with egg, flour, salt, milk and cold cuts.
Pour into well-greased 8-inch pie plate. Bake 30 minutes at 525°.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients into pie pan.
Combine oil and milk into cup and pour over dry ingredients and mix fork to dampen press evenly with fingers to line the pan and sides prick with fork, Bake 10-15 minutes at 425 degrees.
Cool and fill.

title: squash pickles
directions: Soak squash, peppers and onions with salt and water to cover for 1 hour.
Mix spices, sugar and vinegar and bring to boil.
Add drained squash, peppers and onions and bring to a good rolling boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: sugarless banana walnut cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat bananas and butter until creamy. Add eggs.
Beat well. Combine flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon. Add to banana mixture alternately with water.
Beat well after each addition. Stir in nuts. Spoon into a greased 9-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tests done.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 bread, 1/2 fruit, 2 fat for 1 serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Thaw dough and pull apart.
Roll into a half dollar size. Place a little bit of cheese and a piece of beef in each piece. Seal up tight into a half moon shape.
Dip in melted butter and place in a tube pan.
Continue with the rest of the bread, cheese and beef.
Let rise until double in size, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Turn out onto a plate and invert it to another.
Pull apart and enjoy.
Nice fill in with soup and salad dinner.

title: savory cheddar spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add Cheddar cheese and onions; mix well.
Spoon into 9-inch pie pan; top with combined bacon and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with additional crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix coconut and pecans.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 pan.
Put nuts and coconut in pan.
Mix cake by directions.
Put over nuts and coconut.
Beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Drop small spoonfuls over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ice cream wafers
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar. Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mississippi mud brownies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Melt margarine and cocoa together. Remove from heat and stir in sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Immediately cover with marshmallows.
Top with icing while still hot.
Cool.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Warm milk and remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, shortening, salt and vanilla.
Measure warm water into a bowl and add yeast. Mix until dissolved.
Add warm milk mixture to the yeast.
Stir in beaten eggs and 4 cups of flour.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled.
Stir down and add remaining 2 cups of flour. Knead lightly to shape into a smooth ball.
Divide dough.
Roll each half into a circle 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with a doughnut cutter.
Place on a flat surface covered with waxed paper.
Cover with towel.
Let rise in a warm place free from draft until double in bulk.
About 30 minutes.
Fry in deep fat at 360° until golden brown.
Turn once.
Dip in powdered sugar, sugar-syrup or sugar and cinnamon while still warm.

title: fudgey mint cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate with 1/2 cup margarine. In bowl, combine chocolate mixture with sugar, 3 eggs, vanilla and flour.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Place all ingredients in blender except gelatin and cold water. Blend well. Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes. Dissolve over hot water.
Add gelatin to mixture slowly.
May be molded for salad or served as hors d'oeuvres. Garnish with olives and parsley.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: david's delight
directions: Mix flour, butter, walnuts and sugar. Spread in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool. Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and spread over crust. Mix both puddings and milk, then spread on as the next layer. On top, spread remainder of Cool Whip. Sprinkle with shaved chocolate. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place chicken in crock-pot. Add 1 cup water. Layer vegetables. Sprinkle seasonings on top. Cook on low for approximately 8 hours or cook on high for 5 1/2 hours. Serve on top of rice.

title: sandy c.'s asparagus casserole
directions: In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer in order given the ingredients, 3 times.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (no salt) and debone.
Mix Cheez Whiz, broth and soup.
Simmer over low to medium heat until smooth.
Place chips in casserole dish.
Place chicken over chips.
Pour mixture over chips and chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: create a casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Combine mayonnaise, milk, soup and cheese.
Add dry mustard. Gently stir in tuna and then pasta. Place into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on casserole and bake 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Heat oil in heavy nonstick saucepan. Add onion and saute until translucent. Add ground beef and saute until brown.
Drain fat. Add shredded cabbage, paprika, brown sugar, vinegar and salt. Stir well. Add tomato sauce. Simmer all ingredients over low heat 30 to 40 minutes. Serve over rice of your choice.

title: bar-b-q sauce seasoning
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Use for all your barbecue: chicken, beef or pork.

title: doughnut puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients except last two (oil and sugar).
Heat oil.
Drop batter by teaspoonful into oil; cook until golden. Drain on paper.
Roll in sugar.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Set aside.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream together all ingredients.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grannie's brownies
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat with a mixer for 5 minutes on high speed.
Add cocoa and flour into egg and sugar mixture; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Fits an 8 x 8-inch pan or double and use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed. Cook Minute rice and add Cheez Whiz as it is finished.
Put rice and Cheez Whiz in the bottom of pan. Layer on top cooked broccoli.
Soup, directly from can, is next layer. Top with cracker crumbs and 1/2 stick butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: greta perry's salsa
directions: Mix all together.
Let chill for 1/2 hour.

title: janelle's french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in jar (quart size).
Shake well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in a sauce pan. Add water and stir until sugar is dissolved. Stir in blueberries. Cook over medium heat until sauce is slightly thickened and clear. Makes about 2 cups of sauce. Serve warm over pancakes, waffles or cold over ice cream.

title: hearty minestrone
directions: In large
soup
pot
saute onions and garlic in oil and margarine.
Stir
in
carrots, potatoes and celery.
Add green beans, zucchini
and
cabbage.
Cook
until
onions turn soft. Add broth, water
and tomatoes (that you cut up) with juice to pot. Stir
in seasonings.
Simmer uncovered for 2 hours.
Add beans and cook 30 minutes longer.
If small pasta is desired, add to soup at last 20 minutes and cook until tender.

title: rock cookies
directions: Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: In a bowl, combine the eggs and tomato juice.
Stir in the bread crumbs, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Add ground beef and mix well.
On waxed paper or foil, pat meat into a 10 x 8-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices atop meat, leaving a small margin around edges.
Reserve 1 slice of cheese.
Tear up remaining cheese and sprinkle over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat, using paper to lift.
Seal edges and ends. Place roll, seam side down, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: pan de polvo(sand tarts)
directions: Mix in big bowl the flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add lard; mix well.
Simmer tea for about 15 minutes and work into dough. Roll in a ball; slightly pat to flatten.
Bake for about 12 minutes.
While hot, roll in a sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: easy meatballs
directions: Combine first five ingredients with only 2/3 c. manwich sauce.
Mix well.
Reserve the leftover sauce and set aside.
Roll meatballs and arrange in a well greased baking dish.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.
Drain fat.
Pour remaining manwich sauce on top of the meatballs and bake for 15 more minutes.
Serve in a chafing dish or crock pot with fancy toothpicks.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Mix the sugar and Karo and just bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Spread evenly in 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread on bars.
These are good enough without the melted chips.

title: fruit cake
directions: Top with big red cherries and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or so.

title: lizzie's snowball cookies
directions: Cream margarine or butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in the milk a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour with salt and sugar.
Add a little at a time to the creamed mixture.
Add pecans and mix well.
Roll dough (about 1 teaspoon for each cookie) between palm of hands.
Place on floured cookie sheet and bake in a 325° oven for about 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Roll cookies in confectioners sugar while still warm.
Yields 4 or 5 dozen small cookies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Sift flour, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg, allspice and soda.
Add to pumpkin mix alternately with water.
Mix well, then add nuts.
Bake in well-greased and floured pans 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Makes 2 large loaves or 3 (1 pound) coffee cans.

title: barbecue wienies
directions: Will also need toothpicks and foil paper.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10x4 inch bundt pan.
Throughly stir together the flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, mixer at medium speed, beat together the oil, sugar (granulated) eggs and vanilla until combined.
Gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Turn into
prepared pan. Bake in a preheated 325° oven until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean - 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Place cake in pan on a wire rack to cool for 20 minutes.
About 5 minutes, before the cake has finished cooling, in
a small pan, stirring constantly, bring the butter, brown sugar and milk to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
With a small spatula loosen cake edges and around tube.
Turn out on cake plate.
At once spoon the hot sugar mixture over the cake allowing it to run down the sides.
Cool completely.
Cake may be stored a day or two in covered cake box; for longer storage cover and refrigerate, but bring to room temperature before serving.

title: parmesan baked potatoes
directions: Pour margarine into a 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over margarine. Place potatoes with cut side down over cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 45 minutes until tender.

title: rocky road halloween squares
directions: In top of double boiler over boiling water, melt chocolate chips with Eagle Brand milk and butter.
Remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in chocolate mixture.
Spread in wax paper-lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off wax paper.
Cut into squares.
Cover and store at room temperature.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Place chuck roast in crock pot. Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl. Pour mixture over roast. Cover and cook on low 8 - 10 hours, or 4 - 5 hours on high. Remove roast from crock pot; shred meat with fork. Place shredded meat back in crock pot and stir to evenly coat with sauce. Spoon meat onto buns and top with additional sauce, if desired. Serves 12.

title: applesauce-raisin cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar together until fluffy.
Add salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add the eggs and beat for 2 minutes.
Stir in flour, soda, applesauce, raisins and nuts, blending with a spoon.
Pour into a tube pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: meringue
directions: Combine water, cornstarch, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Cook on low heat, stirring until clear and thick.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding remainder or sugar.
Add cooled, cooked mixture, a spoonful at a time, while continuing to beat.
Add desired flavoring.

title: homemade hominy
directions: Cook 45 minutes.
Rinse good, then cook 3 to 4 hours. Pressure 45 minutes on 10 pounds pressure.
Add 1 teaspoon salt per quart.

title: delicious soup
directions: Saute onion and ground beef until beef is pink.
Add other ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Combine pretzels, 2 tablespoons sugar, pecans and butter. Press in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Wash seeds from a pumpkin and pat dry.
Spread on a buttered cookie sheet.
Toast at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and eat.
Kids love them.

title: new orleans wine sauced chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Dredge chicken in this mixture.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend at high speed until all ingredients are mixed well.

title: german sweet chocolate pecan pie
directions: Beat cream cheese in large bowl of electric mixer at high speed until smooth.
Add half and half and beat at low speed until well mixed.
Add pie filling mix; beat until well blended 1 minute.
Fold in whipped topping, chocolate and pecans.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours or overnight. Remove from freezer and let stand about 20 minutes to soften before serving.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: broccoli-cheese chicken
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove; set aside.

title: irvin s. cobb's famous mint julep
directions: Put 12 sprigs of fresh mint in bowl.
Cover the mint with powdered sugar and just enough water to dissolve the sugar. Crush the mint leave with a wooden spoon.
Spoon half the crushed mint and liquid into a drinking glass, sterling cup or pewter mug for your special guests.
Fill the drinking container half full of finely crushed ice.
Add your finest Kentucky bourbon until the container is full.
Refrigerate each full container for 1 to 3 hours before consumption; the real secret to the distinctive taste of the famous Mint Julep.
Decorate with sprigs of mint covered with powdered sugar when ready to serve.
Guaranteed to make you start singing "Dixie."

title: italian crescent crostata
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into 8 rectangles.
Separate 5 of the rectangles into 10 triangles.
Place the 10 triangles in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2-inch up sides to form crust.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Crumble up sausage in skillet.
Add onion and brown.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients and mix together well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, carrots and cheese.
Mix together and put in a casserole dish.
Top with a box of croutons.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, onion and parsley.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Mix well. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Grind steaks, potato and onion together.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly; shape into small balls and fry in 2 tablespoons of shortening.
Do not fry hard.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In a skillet, mix together sugar and cocoa. Add water and bring to a boil for about 30 seconds or less. Serve over hot biscuits.

title: one pot beef stew
directions: Slow cook in crock pot 8 hours or 4 hours on high.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add cooked broccoli, rice (uncooked), soup, water, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form into 1-inch balls with wet or floured hands.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Great to fix ahead of time and freeze.
Makes great hors d'oeuvres, especially around holiday time.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Spread pecans in bottom of pie shell, pour filling over pecans.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: syracuse style caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, butter, cream of tartar and salt. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil rapidly for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda thoroughly and quickly.
Pour at once over popped corn in large (I use disposable) roasting pan.
Stir gently until all kernels are coated.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir 2 to 3 times during baking. Turn at once on wax paper, spread apart and cool.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: cherry blintz salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in pie filling.
Turn into greased shallow 3-quart dish; chill until firm.

title: steak teriyaki
directions: Mix marinade ingredients and green onions.
Marinate 2 flank steaks or skirt steak overnight.
Broil or grill for 7 minutes on each side.	Cut steak across the grain and at an angle for tenderness.

title: popovers
directions: Beat eggs; add milk.
Mix.
Add flour and salt.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Do not open oven.
Reduce heat to 350° for 25 minutes.

title: beverly's yummy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Spread half the mixture in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes.
Remove; sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Combine caramels and remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a saucepan and heat, stirring, until caramels are melted. Drizzle caramel mixture over cake.
Crumble remaining cake mixture on top and bake 20 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: salad dressing
directions: Beat ingredients together slowly at first, then high speed until thickened.
Keeps several weeks in refrigerator.
(Note: Have vinegar and oil at room temperature.) Sprinkle with bacon bits and hard-cooked eggs if desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients (except instant pudding) together; then add pudding.
Can add sliced bananas just before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni as package directs.
Put egg in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer macaroni and cheese until you've used all ingredients.
Fill halfway with milk.
Bake, uncovered, for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, add 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 1 can shoestring potatoes.

title: camper's cocoa
directions: Mix together and keep in airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: mini meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, salt, egg, 1/2 can tomato sauce, Italian seasoning and 1/2 can fried onions.
Make 3 small meat loaves; place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place potatoes around loaves. Bake covered at 375° for 35 minutes.
Place vegetables around loaves and mix with potatoes; add remaining tomato sauce to loaves.
Salt and pepper.
Bake 15 minutes uncovered; add remaining fried onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: sex in a pan
directions: Cream flour, margarine, powdered sugar and nuts together. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° and cool.
Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla and spread over crust.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces.
Pat dry.
Blend together the flour, oil, salt, pepper and paprika. Spread this coating over chicken pieces. Arrange in shallow pan. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: corn scallop
directions: Combine corn and all ingredients, except cheese and paprika. Mix thoroughly and turn into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until mixture is set and top is golden brown.

title: cucumber dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine cottage cheese, cucumber, salt, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice. Mix well and chill until serving.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly. Pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve warm.
Serves 12.

title: rice pilau
directions: Fry pineapple (drained) and raisins in 3 tablespoons margarine until lightly browned.
In another pan, fry onions in remaining margarine until soft; stir in coriander and pepper and fry for 2 minutes.
Add rice and pineapple, then add base and water; cook, stirring occasionally, until rice is soft.
Add more water if needed.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread on 12-inch round tray.
Put salsa on top, then cheese.

title: stew in a pumpkin(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add the onion and cook 1 minute.
Add the garlic and cook until onion is soft, about 8 minutes.
Transfer to a plate and set aside.
Add the meat to the saucepan and saute until browned on all sides.
Add the tomatoes, green pepper, potatoes, salt, pepper, honey, broth and reserved onion.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer gently 1 hour.

title: fruit soup
directions: Boil water, sugar and tapioca until thick and clear.
Add all other ingredients, except bananas.
Best to refrigerate a few hours prior to serving, then add bananas.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine until golden.
Add flour and slowly stir in milk until creamy and thick.
Continue adding milk and water alternately to sauce as it thickens.
Add potatoes and spices to taste.
Continue to cook, stirring so it does not stick. When potatoes are fully cooked, add 2 chopped up hard-boiled eggs.
Simmer another 10 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread and tossed salad.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb, pineapple juice and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in jello; cool.
Add chopped apples and nuts. Serve with Cream Cheese Dressing.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Grease one pound coffee can well; fill 2/3 full.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Tie with string.
Steam at least 2 1/2 hours.
Take out of water and cool. Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Place chicken, cheese and onions in tortillas and roll up. Place in 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Place, seam side down.
Set aside.

title: chicken poppy seed
directions: Cook chicken in crock-pot until done. Break up into small pieces. Mix together the soup and sour cream. Layer chicken, then soup and sour cream mixture. Crush the crackers and toss with the melted butter. Spread on top. Sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve with salad and rolls.

title: pasta and vegetable salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, except substitute chicken soup mix for the salt.
Drain and cool.
Add cucumbers, tomato, onion and green pepper.
Pour enough Sweet Herb Dressing over salad to moisten.
Refrigerate several hours.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all together well and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter date squares
directions: Cut dates in pieces.
Cream peanut butter, margarine and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until light. Press into greased 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: pizza patties
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into patties.
Grill until done.
Serve on hamburger rolls.
